WEBVTT

1
00:00:17.160 --> 00:00:21.839
INSPECTOR RICCIARDI

2
00:00:24.520 --> 00:00:27.520
APPLAUSE AND WHISTLING

3
00:00:31.120 --> 00:00:33.119
I love to walk along. via Toledo

4
00:00:33.440 --> 00:00:35.879
How come I haven't seen
Emma for 2 days?

5
00:00:36.760 --> 00:00:38.359
Did she get sick
of seeing your face?

6
00:00:40.840 --> 00:00:43.839
Who's that?
What is he? Who is he?

7
00:00:44.360 --> 00:00:47.279
- Here's the handsome Fefe!

8
00:00:47.320 --> 00:00:48.760
LAUGHTER

9
00:00:52.440 --> 00:00:53.599
Ah. yes!

10
00:00:56.120 --> 00:00:59.319
There's nothing I can do
if I shine in the world

11
00:01:00.120 --> 00:01:02.959
I'm athletic. elegant.
wise. practical and brilliant

12
00:01:03.720 --> 00:01:06.559
Where is he?
What is he? Who is he?

13
00:01:07.200 --> 00:01:09.239
Here's the handsome Fefe!

14
00:01:09.600 --> 00:01:13.559
I love to walk along via Toledo
and the seafront

15
00:01:14.040 --> 00:01:17.119
I love to walk with Fefe!

16
00:01:17.880 --> 00:01:19.720
APPLAUSE

17
00:01:20.920 --> 00:01:23.319
TO MY DEAR EMMA.
ATTILIO

18
00:01:45.720 --> 00:01:47.039
Munaciello!

19
00:01:48.880 --> 00:01:50.439
Talk to me!

20
00:02:09.479 --> 00:02:10.919
Emma. it's useless.

21
00:02:11.039 --> 00:02:13.999
We could do it ten or a hundred times.
it'll always be the same.

22
00:02:15.040 --> 00:02:17.119
You can't control the cards.

23
00:02:18.040 --> 00:02:20.039
But you know
what you need to do.

24
00:02:20.400 --> 00:02:24.199
- But I can't. I can't.
- No. You have to.

25
00:02:24.880 --> 00:02:28.319
This is you.
you have to do it. and quickly.

26
00:02:28.680 --> 00:02:31.839
Otherwise misfortune will strike.
understand? Misfortune!

27
00:02:39.600 --> 00:02:41.359
Emma. it's useless.

28
00:02:41.480 --> 00:02:43.799
If the horse of clubs
isn't destined to come out.

29
00:02:44.240 --> 00:02:45.839
it won't. understand?

30
00:03:39.560 --> 00:03:41.560
SHOUTING INSIDE

31
00:03:41.600 --> 00:03:42.600
DOG BARKS

32
00:03:57.000 --> 00:04:00.000
HE PANTS

33
00:04:26.960 --> 00:04:27.960
Tonino.

34
00:04:29.600 --> 00:04:30.959
What are you doing still up?

35
00:04:31.520 --> 00:04:33.799
I was waiting for you.
Did something happen?

36
00:04:34.360 --> 00:04:36.919
No. I've got a fever. Concetta.
It's just a fever.

37
00:04:39.120 --> 00:04:40.239
Go to bed.

38
00:04:49.000 --> 00:04:53.000
DOOR OPENS AND CLOSES

39
00:05:00.560 --> 00:05:03.039
- Is Emma back?
- Yes.

40
00:05:04.000 --> 00:05:06.359
I made you dinner.
shall I heat it up for you?

41
00:05:09.320 --> 00:05:12.159
You didn't see me. Teresa.
Is that clear?

42
00:05:25.240 --> 00:05:26.319
Inspector.

43
00:05:26.480 --> 00:05:30.439
we just got word of a woman killed
in the Sanita neighbourhood.

44
00:05:31.080 --> 00:05:35.359
A certain Carmela Calise.
an old fortune teller.

45
00:05:38.240 --> 00:05:39.959
- Has Maione arrived?
- No. Inspector.

46
00:05:40.400 --> 00:05:42.559
- He starts later today.
- Thank you.

47
00:05:54.360 --> 00:05:56.279
Lucia. why-didn't you
wake me up?

48
00:05:57.320 --> 00:05:59.759
You said you could go in
2 hours later today.

49
00:06:03.440 --> 00:06:04.719
Exactly.

50
00:06:05.920 --> 00:06:08.679
The kids are at school.
That hasn't happened in ages.

51
00:06:10.440 --> 00:06:12.279
We could have spent
some time together.

52
00:06:12.400 --> 00:06:14.239
You clearly-needed to sleep.

53
00:06:21.640 --> 00:06:25.559
Donna Carmela!
Donna Carmela has been killed!

54
00:06:25.680 --> 00:06:27.759
She's been killed!
Her head was smashed open

55
00:06:27.880 --> 00:06:30.959
Let me through. Move aside!
Move aside. come on.

56
00:06:31.840 --> 00:06:33.119
Move aside.

57
00:06:33.240 --> 00:06:36.199
- What happened?
- Come on. Inspector. she's over here.

58
00:06:36.440 --> 00:06:40.279
- You are?
- Nunzia Petrone. the caretaker.

59
00:06:40.920 --> 00:06:43.399
Did you see or hear
anything strange last night?

60
00:06:43.840 --> 00:06:45.639
- Then get' out of here.

61
00:06:46.240 --> 00:06:48.639
Camarda. go and call Modo.
And don't let anyone in.

62
00:06:48.760 --> 00:06:49.799
Cesarano.

63
00:06:51.120 --> 00:06:55.199
This morning I went upstairs
to get my daughter. Antonietta.

64
00:06:55.600 --> 00:06:58.519
Sometimes she sleeps
at Donna Carmela's house.

65
00:06:59.720 --> 00:07:01.999
She's the only one
who watches her when I'm at work.

66
00:07:02.760 --> 00:07:05.079
- What time was it?
- 8:30am.

67
00:07:08.120 --> 00:07:11.199
Everyone go. didn't you hear
the Inspector? Come on.

68
00:07:12.040 --> 00:07:13.439
Don't you understand?

69
00:07:13.680 --> 00:07:16.919
When I went in.
I saw blood everywhere:

70
00:07:17.360 --> 00:07:18.919
Was the door open?

71
00:07:19.040 --> 00:07:22.479
Yes. Donna Carmela's door
was always open.

72
00:07:22.680 --> 00:07:24.239
We're like family here.

73
00:07:25.760 --> 00:07:27.359
Trust me. Inspector.

74
00:07:28.240 --> 00:07:32.039
the depraved coward who did this
doesn't live in the building

75
00:07:32.160 --> 00:07:33.559
or in the neighbourhood.

76
00:07:34.040 --> 00:07:37.039
Donna Carmela was a saint.
Everybody loved her.

77
00:07:37.240 --> 00:07:40.439
- A saint who told fortunes?
- What's wrong with that?

78
00:07:41.480 --> 00:07:43.919
She helped people.
she gave them hope.

79
00:07:44.640 --> 00:07:45.759
Come with me.

80
00:07:49.040 --> 00:07:50.479
This way. Inspector.

81
00:07:52.520 --> 00:07:53.799
Almost there.

82
00:07:57.120 --> 00:07:58.519
Here we are.

83
00:07:59.080 --> 00:08:02.519
- There's someone inside. who is it?
- My daughter Antonietta.

84
00:08:03.800 --> 00:08:05.439
She's backwards. Inspector.

85
00:08:06.400 --> 00:08:08.599
But she loved Donna Carmela.

86
00:08:08.840 --> 00:08:12.199
- She doesn't want to come out.
- Fine. let her be.

87
00:08:12.560 --> 00:08:14.839
When was the last time
you saw the lady alive?

88
00:08:14.960 --> 00:08:17.159
Last night. around 10.

89
00:08:17.600 --> 00:08:19.719
My daughter and I came up.
like every evening.

90
00:08:19.840 --> 00:08:22.999
How was she? Nervous. worried?
Anything out of the ordinary?

91
00:08:23.120 --> 00:08:27.039
No. no. She even said goodbye.
She said: "See you tomorrow."

92
00:08:27.640 --> 00:08:29.039
And this morning...

93
00:08:30.000 --> 00:08:31.719
Cesarano. don't let anyone in.

94
00:08:33.040 --> 00:08:35.040
SHE SOBS

95
00:08:37.840 --> 00:08:39.519
Poor woman...

96
00:09:22.480 --> 00:09:26.039
God is not a merchant
who pays on Saturday.

97
00:09:26.880 --> 00:09:30.359
God is not a merchant
who pays on Saturday.

98
00:09:31.560 --> 00:09:34.799
God is not a merchant
who pays on Saturday.

99
00:09:36.680 --> 00:09:39.839
God is not a merchant
who pays on Saturday.

100
00:09:40.320 --> 00:09:44.159
God is not a merchant
who pays on Saturday.

101
00:09:47.880 --> 00:09:49.599
Want a braid of garlic?

102
00:09:49.720 --> 00:09:50.720
WOMAN SHRIEKS

103
00:09:54.080 --> 00:09:55.839
Annina! Annina!

104
00:09:59.400 --> 00:10:00.679
What is it?

105
00:10:04.320 --> 00:10:06.559
Blood... What was that?

106
00:10:07.920 --> 00:10:09.959
- Madam. did you scream?
- Yes.

107
00:10:10.720 --> 00:10:11.799
Calm down.

108
00:10:17.280 --> 00:10:18.959
- Who is it?
- Her name's Filomena.

109
00:10:19.160 --> 00:10:21.319
- Filomena?
- Filomena the whore!

110
00:10:21.760 --> 00:10:24.119
No. Filomena Russo.

111
00:10:24.640 --> 00:10:27.239
Did you see anyone come out?

112
00:10:27.480 --> 00:10:28.639
Stay here>

113
00:10:32.080 --> 00:10:33.399
Madam?

114
00:10:34.560 --> 00:10:36.039
Madam. are you alone?

115
00:10:44.240 --> 00:10:45.359
Madam.

116
00:10:52.400 --> 00:10:53.719
Is anyone home?

117
00:10:58.040 --> 00:10:59.199
Madam.

118
00:11:00.560 --> 00:11:01.639
Miss Filomena!

119
00:11:06.160 --> 00:11:08.999
Oh goodness. what happened?
Who did this to you?

120
00:11:12.160 --> 00:11:15.079
I'll take care of you.
Hold this. press hard.

121
00:11:15.520 --> 00:11:17.039
It's all right. don't worry.

122
00:11:19.440 --> 00:11:20.799
Why don't we call a doctor?

123
00:11:22.520 --> 00:11:25.559
Call a doctor. My God!

124
00:11:25.920 --> 00:11:27.479
I don't know who it was.

125
00:11:27.600 --> 00:11:31.119
Look at all that blood!
Good Lord. help her!

126
00:11:31.960 --> 00:11:34.479
I didn't see anything.
Oh God!

127
00:11:37.040 --> 00:11:39.040
PHONE RINGS

128
00:11:47.320 --> 00:11:50.079
Teresa!
Don't answer. Teresa!

129
00:11:51.760 --> 00:11:53.279
I'm right here. madam.

130
00:11:57.920 --> 00:11:59.959
- Has my husband gone out?

131
00:12:00.640 --> 00:12:02.639
The driver asked
if he should prepare the car.

132
00:12:03.200 --> 00:12:06.239
No. no car.
Clean up the room. hurry.

133
00:12:11.600 --> 00:12:13.640
PHONE CONTINUES TO RING

134
00:12:24.320 --> 00:12:27.279
I'm looking for Emma Serra.
This is Attilio Romolo.

135
00:12:29.680 --> 00:12:30.680
Emma. is that you?

136
00:12:32.120 --> 00:12:33.120
SHE SOBS

137
00:12:35.080 --> 00:12:36.359
Here we are.

138
00:12:37.400 --> 00:12:39.159
- Doctor!
- Maione.

139
00:12:39.360 --> 00:12:41.719
- Maione. what happened? Put her here.

140
00:12:42.520 --> 00:12:44.359
Sister. a stretcher. hurry.

141
00:12:47.200 --> 00:12:51.079
What happened? I was on my way to you.
but I thought it was for a dead woman.

142
00:12:51.520 --> 00:12:54.359
Sorry. doctor. but I don't know
what you're talking about.

143
00:12:54.480 --> 00:12:57.439
I haven't been
down to the station yet.

144
00:12:57.560 --> 00:13:01.319
No? Then go to Ricciardi.
He's in Sanita. here's the address.

145
00:13:01.440 --> 00:13:04.479
- We'll talk later. First the living.
- Thank you. doctor.

146
00:13:16.240 --> 00:13:18.719
- Good morning. Inspector.
- Maione. welcome.

147
00:13:18.880 --> 00:13:20.799
- Was getting worried.
- Sorry.

148
00:13:20.920 --> 00:13:23.879
I had to help a woman
who was injured.

149
00:13:24.160 --> 00:13:26.959
Sorry I'm late.
Dr Modo will be late too.

150
00:13:32.000 --> 00:13:33.319
Jesus. Inspector.

151
00:13:34.520 --> 00:13:38.359
- Who's behind this massacre?
- Someone with no heart.

152
00:13:39.560 --> 00:13:41.559
He even traipsed
through the blood.

153
00:13:42.320 --> 00:13:44.439
He seems to have slipped there.

154
00:13:44.640 --> 00:13:47.119
The footprints could be
from more than one person.

155
00:13:54.840 --> 00:13:55.840
Inspector.

156
00:14:03.680 --> 00:14:05.239
Look what I've found.

157
00:14:09.560 --> 00:14:11.959
Dates and times
of her appointments.

158
00:14:12.360 --> 00:14:14.039
She was a fortune teller.

159
00:14:15.640 --> 00:14:17.399
"Lovine. dead father."

160
00:14:17.920 --> 00:14:19.959
"Del Giudice.
husband who beats her."

161
00:14:20.920 --> 00:14:23.879
Grammar aside. this book tells her
clients' futures. Good job. Cesarano.

162
00:14:30.360 --> 00:14:34.439
"Auriemma. broken knife grinder.
Iovine. bakery. blood to blood."

163
00:14:41.480 --> 00:14:43.519
- Raffaele.
- Inspector.

164
00:14:46.120 --> 00:14:47.599
Yesterday's page.

165
00:14:48.360 --> 00:14:50.199
"Passarelli. old mother.

166
00:14:51.040 --> 00:14:54.119
"Ridolfi. boy. jewellery. wife.

167
00:14:54.560 --> 00:14:57.239
"Colombo. girl. new. love.

168
00:14:57.840 --> 00:14:58.840
"Emma.

169
00:15:00.280 --> 00:15:01.919
Lodice. pay."

170
00:15:02.760 --> 00:15:04.799
These are the last people
to have seen her alive.

171
00:15:04.920 --> 00:15:06.879
besides the caretaker
and her daughter.

172
00:15:07.000 --> 00:15:08.519
We have to find out
who they are.

173
00:15:22.480 --> 00:15:25.479
What is it. Tonino?
Are you expecting someone?

174
00:15:29.520 --> 00:15:30.520
Tonino.

175
00:15:33.760 --> 00:15:36.319
Why don't you tell
your Concetta what's up?

176
00:15:37.360 --> 00:15:39.919
The only problem is
the customers who don't come.

177
00:15:41.200 --> 00:15:42.879
I'm just hoping more will come.

178
00:15:56.320 --> 00:15:58.999
Why don't they commit murders
on the ground floor?

179
00:15:59.720 --> 00:16:02.119
- Bruno. good morning. About time.
- Good morning.

180
00:16:02.440 --> 00:16:06.559
Reprimanding me.
after I saved the Sergeant's friend?

181
00:16:06.720 --> 00:16:08.199
- Friend?
- No. Inspector.

182
00:16:09.400 --> 00:16:10.519
Not a friend.

183
00:16:11.560 --> 00:16:13.839
- She's the lady I helped this morning.
- Whatever.

184
00:16:15.080 --> 00:16:16.599
How's she doing?

185
00:16:16.720 --> 00:16:20.839
I gave her the best stitches I could.
but the scar will remain. Poor thing.

186
00:16:21.080 --> 00:16:22.879
Pretty woman indeed.
what a shame.

187
00:16:23.240 --> 00:16:25.759
- Who was the jerk who did this?
- Don't know yet.

188
00:16:27.760 --> 00:16:30.479
Hey. Maiane. are you blushing

189
00:16:30.600 --> 00:16:33.119
- Blushing. doctor?
- You're turning red!

190
00:16:33.240 --> 00:16:34.959
- Have you fallen in love?
- What?

191
00:16:35.080 --> 00:16:37.959
Leave him alone. He's a great
policeman with a lovely family.

192
00:16:38.080 --> 00:16:41.639
- not lonely and desperate like us.
- He's like a lover in springtime.

193
00:16:41.760 --> 00:16:44.039
- You can see it in his eyes.
- You cannot!

194
00:16:45.040 --> 00:16:46.599
We'll discharge her tonight.

195
00:16:47.560 --> 00:16:49.239
Let's see what happened here.>

196
00:16:50.320 --> 00:16:53.919
They went all out. didn't they?
This is going to take a long time.

197
00:16:57.360 --> 00:16:58.360
So...

198
00:17:02.520 --> 00:17:05.799
God is not a merchant
who pays on Saturday.

199
00:17:07.000 --> 00:17:10.559
God is not a merchant
who pays on Saturday.

200
00:17:11.960 --> 00:17:15.639
God is not a merchant
who pays on Saturday.

201
00:17:32.680 --> 00:17:36.559
A fortune teller and a loan shark.
Here's the last promissory note.

202
00:17:37.720 --> 00:17:40.279
She gave hope with one hand
and took it away with the other.

203
00:17:40.400 --> 00:17:42.439
She did magic tricks.
a magician!

204
00:17:42.960 --> 00:17:44.919
This isn't very funny. Raffaele.

205
00:17:45.360 --> 00:17:48.159
With all these debtors.
anyone could have killed her.

206
00:17:51.200 --> 00:17:52.200
But...

207
00:17:53.000 --> 00:17:56.599
if the murderer got blood all over
everything and left the money.

208
00:17:57.520 --> 00:17:59.199
he was looking for
something else.

209
00:18:01.080 --> 00:18:03.439
He was probably looking for
his own promissory note.

210
00:18:03.920 --> 00:18:06.999
So if he found it. then
all these papers are useless to us.

211
00:18:07.120 --> 00:18:09.999
- We won't find the murderer in here.

212
00:18:13.160 --> 00:18:15.079
Let's concentrate on these.

213
00:18:16.440 --> 00:18:19.319
We'll get the list of all the people
with these surnames

214
00:18:19.340 --> 00:18:21.016
in the neighbourhood
and in the whole city.

215
00:18:21.040 --> 00:18:23.919
and we'll talk to every one of them.
We'll find them.

216
00:18:24.800 --> 00:18:26.999
- Will do.
- Tomorrow though.

217
00:18:28.000 --> 00:18:31.879
Now. let's just write up a report
and go home.

218
00:18:32.560 --> 00:18:35.319
Inspector. with your permission.
I'll be going now.

219
00:18:35.680 --> 00:18:37.199
I've got something
to take care of.

220
00:18:39.280 --> 00:18:40.479
Go ahead.

221
00:18:45.560 --> 00:18:46.560
Thank you.

222
00:18:52.840 --> 00:18:57.039
- Sergeant. I have to thank you.
- Don't mention it. madam.

223
00:18:57.760 --> 00:18:59.559
I was just doing my duty.

224
00:19:00.520 --> 00:19:02.599
But now I have to ask you
some questions.

225
00:19:03.280 --> 00:19:07.759
A crime was committed
and I can't pretend it didn't happen.

226
00:19:08.600 --> 00:19:09.959
No. Sergeant.

227
00:19:10.880 --> 00:19:12.559
I don't want to report anyone.

228
00:19:13.880 --> 00:19:16.119
You found me by chance
and I'm happy about that.

229
00:19:16.240 --> 00:19:17.959
But I wouldn't have called you.

230
00:19:21.280 --> 00:19:25.079
Now if you'll excuse me.
my son must be worried.

231
00:19:26.960 --> 00:19:30.039
Fine. for today we'll leave it.
It's getting late. anyway.

232
00:19:31.800 --> 00:19:33.079
But think about it.

233
00:19:35.880 --> 00:19:37.519
You've been seriously injured.

234
00:19:38.800 --> 00:19:41.759
You'll never look the same.
do you understand that?

235
00:19:43.920 --> 00:19:47.239
See. Sergeant?
Spring's here.

236
00:19:48.800 --> 00:19:50.399
Enjoy the evening.

237
00:19:53.440 --> 00:19:54.759
And thanks again.

238
00:19:58.800 --> 00:20:01.800
INDISTINCT CHATTER

239
00:20:13.720 --> 00:20:17.279
Good evening. Sergeant.
Going to have some fun tonight?

240
00:20:23.680 --> 00:20:25.599
Sergeant. what a surprise

241
00:20:27.000 --> 00:20:30.319
If you'd told me you were coming.
I would have got ready.

242
00:20:31.640 --> 00:20:35.239
Bambinella.
not even black magic can help you.

243
00:20:36.840 --> 00:20:37.999
Fine.

244
00:20:39.640 --> 00:20:41.119
How can I help you?

245
00:20:41.360 --> 00:20:44.719
I know you're investigating the death
of the fortune teller from Sanita.

246
00:20:44.880 --> 00:20:47.919
Of course you already know that.
You know who the murderer is too?

247
00:20:48.040 --> 00:20:50.959
Jesus! No. Sergeant.
That's your job.

248
00:20:51.080 --> 00:20:53.719
- Thankfully.
- Plus that's not my area.

249
00:20:54.200 --> 00:20:56.319
With all the lowlifes
around there...

250
00:20:56.840 --> 00:20:59.599
All I know is she was really good
at reading cards.

251
00:20:59.960 --> 00:21:02.520
A friend of mine's boyfriend
used to work at a construction site.

252
00:21:02.760 --> 00:21:04.839
and she told her:
"He's not going to work.

253
00:21:04.960 --> 00:21:07.879
he's going to a whorehouse
in Elena Street!" And it was true.

254
00:21:08.400 --> 00:21:10.559
People who believe
these things are stupid.

255
00:21:11.040 --> 00:21:12.879
Calise was a swindler.

256
00:21:14.040 --> 00:21:16.679
First she'd get information.
like I do with you.

257
00:21:16.880 --> 00:21:18.439
Then she'd make prophecies.

258
00:21:18.560 --> 00:21:22.519
Sergeant. sometimes you need
to believe in something.

259
00:21:26.280 --> 00:21:28.159
That's true. Bambinella.

260
00:21:29.320 --> 00:21:31.559
Listen. I also came
to ask you for...

261
00:21:32.760 --> 00:21:37.039
information about a woman from
the Quartieri Spagnoli who was disfigured.

262
00:21:37.360 --> 00:21:39.039
Filomena from Vico Del Fico.

263
00:21:40.160 --> 00:21:43.639
She's the prettiest woman in Naples.
Everybody knows that.

264
00:21:45.480 --> 00:21:48.199
If everybody knows that.
do you also know who disfigured her?

265
00:21:48.800 --> 00:21:52.239
Everyone and no one. Sergeant.
Filomena is a virgin whore.

266
00:21:53.240 --> 00:21:56.239
- What does that mean?
- It's a saying of mine.

267
00:21:57.440 --> 00:21:59.959
Since she’s pretty.
everyone thinks she's a whore.

268
00:22:00.080 --> 00:22:02.559
Actually. she's a virtuous
person. so a virgin.

269
00:22:03.400 --> 00:22:06.399
And since she's a widow.
all of Naples watches her.

270
00:22:06.520 --> 00:22:09.999
There's always someone obsessed
with her who won't leave her alone.

271
00:22:13.880 --> 00:22:14.999
Bambinella.

272
00:22:16.480 --> 00:22:19.559
who is it
that won't leave her alone?

273
00:22:24.800 --> 00:22:28.239
The latest one: a thug
named Don Luigi Costanzo.

274
00:22:29.040 --> 00:22:30.519
A nobody.

275
00:22:33.160 --> 00:22:36.719
Sergeant. if you're obsessed
with someone. you kill them.

276
00:22:36.840 --> 00:22:38.239
You don't disfigure them.

277
00:22:40.000 --> 00:22:41.239
True.

278
00:22:41.800 --> 00:22:43.079
All right.

279
00:22:44.320 --> 00:22:47.079
- Can I tell you one more thing?
- Sure.

280
00:22:48.520 --> 00:22:50.999
Beauty can drive people mad.

281
00:22:51.880 --> 00:22:55.839
- Don't get involved. if I may say so.
- You may not. all right?

282
00:22:56.440 --> 00:22:58.719
This is my job.
My job!

283
00:23:02.400 --> 00:23:03.599
Be good.

284
00:23:07.640 --> 00:23:10.519
There he is.
Did you have fun. Sergeant?

285
00:23:10.800 --> 00:23:12.999
- Shut up or I'll put you in a convent.

286
00:23:13.360 --> 00:23:14.360
SHE LAUGHS

287
00:23:34.600 --> 00:23:35.600
It's Daddy!

288
00:23:37.040 --> 00:23:39.279
- It's Daddy!
- Daddy!

289
00:23:41.080 --> 00:23:42.080
Hi!

290
00:23:43.000 --> 00:23:44.799
- Good evening. Dad.
- Hey. lad.

291
00:23:45.400 --> 00:23:46.839
- Hi. Dad.
- Hi.

292
00:23:48.760 --> 00:23:49.879
So.

293
00:23:50.720 --> 00:23:52.359
- have you been good?
- Yes.

294
00:23:52.480 --> 00:23:55.399
What are you doing up so late?
Go on. go to bed.

295
00:23:55.520 --> 00:23:56.719
Put them to bed.

296
00:24:11.640 --> 00:24:13.079
Lucia. I'm sorry.

297
00:24:14.720 --> 00:24:17.719
I'm sorry I'm late.
There's a new case.

298
00:24:18.400 --> 00:24:21.039
Have you seen?
Spring is coming.

299
00:24:21.840 --> 00:24:25.479
You feel that nice crisp air.
don't you?

300
00:24:31.600 --> 00:24:33.119
I don't feel anything.

301
00:24:35.040 --> 00:24:36.639
Actually. I'm cold.

302
00:24:37.680 --> 00:24:40.680
MUSIC PLAYS

303
00:25:10.120 --> 00:25:11.120
MUSIC STOPS

304
00:25:15.400 --> 00:25:19.839
What? Not only do I have to
wait up for you every evening.

305
00:25:20.400 --> 00:25:22.199
but I can't even
listen to the radio.

306
00:25:22.560 --> 00:25:24.919
- Of course you can.
- Good.

307
00:25:25.120 --> 00:25:28.839
But three mummies woke up at
the National Museum and started dancing.

308
00:25:28.960 --> 00:25:31.279
The director came down
to the station to complain.

309
00:25:31.440 --> 00:25:32.999
Enough wisecracking.

310
00:25:33.440 --> 00:25:38.119
I'm becoming old and deaf.
and it doesn't even cross your mind

311
00:25:38.280 --> 00:25:41.679
to find yourself a good woman
to take care of you instead of me.

312
00:25:41.800 --> 00:25:44.959
Of course not. Where would I find
a woman like you? It's impossible!

313
00:25:45.240 --> 00:25:46.719
Just a moment.

314
00:25:47.480 --> 00:25:52.079
Before dinner. you need to try on
the suit the tailor brought.

315
00:25:52.440 --> 00:25:54.839
When did we decide
to ask the tailor for a new suit?

316
00:25:55.040 --> 00:25:57.519
When? Never!
I took care of it.

317
00:25:57.720 --> 00:26:02.519
You're still the Baron of Malomonte.
and as long as I'm in this house.

318
00:26:02.800 --> 00:26:05.479
you won't go around
dressed like a beggar.

319
00:26:05.640 --> 00:26:07.719
Fine. Can I take off
the old one first?

320
00:26:07.840 --> 00:26:10.519
Yes. I'll heat up your dinner
in the meantime. Go on.

321
00:26:30.000 --> 00:26:32.479
She's sleeping now. but come in.

322
00:26:32.600 --> 00:26:33.959
- Mummy!
- Be quiet.

323
00:26:36.960 --> 00:26:39.519
Darling.
what are you doing here?

324
00:26:40.240 --> 00:26:42.399
I don't want to eat alone.

325
00:26:43.320 --> 00:26:45.119
But Rosa's there with you.

326
00:26:47.600 --> 00:26:52.079
Fine. do you want to have dinner
here. in my room. tonight?

327
00:26:53.760 --> 00:26:57.119
Then Rosa will bring you your plate
and you can sit at that little table.

328
00:27:04.760 --> 00:27:06.119
I knew it!

329
00:27:06.880 --> 00:27:08.239
My poor boy.

330
00:27:09.720 --> 00:27:11.919
You'll have to get used
to being alone.

331
00:27:16.240 --> 00:27:18.399
You'll have to get used
to being alone.

332
00:27:22.000 --> 00:27:26.159
Well? Are we going to try on this suit
before everything gets cold?

333
00:27:26.880 --> 00:27:28.079
Let's try it on.

334
00:28:23.880 --> 00:28:24.919
Good morning.

335
00:28:37.440 --> 00:28:39.479
- Good morning. Sergeant.
- Good morning.

336
00:28:44.880 --> 00:28:47.359
- Good morning. Sergeant.
- Good morning. Filomena.

337
00:28:47.520 --> 00:28:48.999
Sorry it's so early.

338
00:28:49.480 --> 00:28:52.079
- Did you take the bandage off?
- Yes. it was bothering me.

339
00:28:52.200 --> 00:28:53.959
- Bread with tomato?
- No. thank you.

340
00:28:54.080 --> 00:28:55.919
I just came by to ask you...

341
00:28:57.280 --> 00:28:58.759
you'd reconsider.

342
00:29:02.120 --> 00:29:03.519
Listen. I understand.

343
00:29:04.840 --> 00:29:08.119
You might be scared. because
you think someone could hurt you.

344
00:29:08.800 --> 00:29:10.439
But you don't have to worry.

345
00:29:11.920 --> 00:29:14.679
Maybe a man
who thinks you're his.

346
00:29:15.120 --> 00:29:17.559
Jealousy is a nasty beast.
it drives people crazy.

347
00:29:17.680 --> 00:29:19.479
Sergeant.
ever since my husband died.

348
00:29:19.600 --> 00:29:22.239
I haven't been with a single man.
and it's been 2 years!

349
00:29:24.280 --> 00:29:26.359
I'm sorry.
I didn't mean to doubt you.

350
00:29:27.280 --> 00:29:30.439
I just thought maybe
someone had threatened you.

351
00:29:30.880 --> 00:29:34.599
You know what. Sergeant?
You'll be late and so will I.

352
00:29:38.560 --> 00:29:39.839
I told you.

353
00:29:41.240 --> 00:29:42.879
I don't want to report anyone.

354
00:29:52.400 --> 00:29:54.159
Well. what can I say?

355
00:29:55.280 --> 00:29:56.479
If that's what you want..

356
00:29:56.640 --> 00:29:59.239
But I'm warning you.
I'll need to come back.

357
00:29:59.960 --> 00:30:02.959
Until I'm sure you and your son
are not in danger.

358
00:30:04.280 --> 00:30:06.519
You can come back
whenever you like. Sergeant.

359
00:30:09.440 --> 00:30:11.839
- Thanks again.
- Have a nice day.

360
00:30:11.960 --> 00:30:12.960
Have a nice day.

361
00:30:54.880 --> 00:30:56.120
- Morning. Inspector.
- Morning.

362
00:30:56.160 --> 00:30:58.799
I'll make you some coffee substitute.
I need some too.

363
00:30:58.920 --> 00:31:02.199
- You didn't sleep well. Malone?
- No. I got to thinking.

364
00:31:02.480 --> 00:31:06.039
Calise knew all of
her clients' business. But how?

365
00:31:07.200 --> 00:31:10.919
I think we can all have
an informant. right. Inspector?

366
00:31:12.840 --> 00:31:15.799
- You're right. Let's go.
- Where?

367
00:31:16.360 --> 00:31:19.439
To Sanita. Maybe we missed
something or someone.

368
00:31:19.560 --> 00:31:23.119
- The coffee substitute. Inspector?
- I'll buy you a real one at Gambrinus.

369
00:31:23.800 --> 00:31:27.359
God is not a merchant
who pays on Saturday.

370
00:31:28.560 --> 00:31:31.519
God is not a merchant
who pays on Saturday.

371
00:31:33.040 --> 00:31:36.279
God is not a merchant
who pays on Saturday.

372
00:31:36.400 --> 00:31:39.319
What is it. Inspector?
What are you thinking about?

373
00:31:39.960 --> 00:31:40.999
Nothing.

374
00:31:43.720 --> 00:31:46.039
It's not nice to go through
dead people's things.

375
00:31:46.840 --> 00:31:49.239
But I have to say.
you do it respectfully.

376
00:31:50.680 --> 00:31:53.879
- Like Modo when he studies a body.
- Don't exaggerate.

377
00:31:54.000 --> 00:31:56.359
It's an honour
to be compared to Modo. but...

378
00:32:16.880 --> 00:32:19.359
Donna Carmela
helped me out sometimes.

379
00:32:20.200 --> 00:32:22.399
Antonietta really loved her.

380
00:32:22.640 --> 00:32:25.759
She would give her little presents
sometimes. Sweets.

381
00:32:26.000 --> 00:32:29.479
130 lire of sweets. madam?
What’s that. two wheelbarrows full?

382
00:32:29.640 --> 00:32:31.719
Who told you
that money was for me?

383
00:32:32.040 --> 00:32:34.759
You can write anything
on a piece of paper. right?

384
00:32:36.440 --> 00:32:40.079
- You want to find someone to blame.
- You're right.

385
00:32:41.000 --> 00:32:43.639
We need a guilty party.
but we have no evidence.

386
00:32:44.040 --> 00:32:46.519
All we have is
this roll of sweets money.

387
00:32:47.440 --> 00:32:48.759
Know what we'll do?

388
00:32:49.440 --> 00:32:51.919
If you don't tell us the truth.
we'll take you to jail.

389
00:32:52.080 --> 00:32:55.039
accusing you of blackmailing Calise.
and that will be the end of it.

390
00:32:56.000 --> 00:32:57.639
Would you dare to do that?

391
00:32:58.120 --> 00:33:01.839
- And my daughter?
- There are some excellent institutes.

392
00:33:06.960 --> 00:33:08.039
Fine.

393
00:33:10.200 --> 00:33:13.039
It all started a few years ago.

394
00:33:13.760 --> 00:33:17.679
when Donna Carmela got arthritis and
couldn't work as a seamstress anymore.

395
00:33:19.520 --> 00:33:22.799
She told me she knew
how to read cards.

396
00:33:23.280 --> 00:33:25.599
And since I knew a widow
in the neighbourhood

397
00:33:25.720 --> 00:33:28.239
who wouldn't stop talking
about her husband.

398
00:33:29.560 --> 00:33:32.879
I told her that Donna Carmela
could send messages to the afterlife.

399
00:33:33.880 --> 00:33:37.839
Since I knew everything
about the lady. the deal was perfect.

400
00:33:39.080 --> 00:33:42.399
Then the word spread.
and other clients came.

401
00:33:43.400 --> 00:33:45.239
You knew everything
about them too?

402
00:33:54.040 --> 00:33:58.039
When someone I didn't know came.
Donna Carmela found out the name.

403
00:33:58.320 --> 00:34:00.479
the address.
and what they wanted to know.

404
00:34:00.600 --> 00:34:03.399
And then she'd say she was busy
until the following week.

405
00:34:04.560 --> 00:34:06.759
In the meantime.
I collected information.

406
00:34:07.920 --> 00:34:12.039
Inspector.
people arrived sad and left happy.

407
00:34:12.800 --> 00:34:15.559
- We did nothing wrong.
- Except for tricking them.

408
00:34:16.159 --> 00:34:18.799
Earning enough to be able
to start up a usury business.

409
00:34:18.920 --> 00:34:21.719
We found the box with the promissory
notes. don't try to deny it.

410
00:34:22.400 --> 00:34:25.359
Well. that's a way
to help people too. right?

411
00:34:25.480 --> 00:34:27.559
At 3% a month?

412
00:34:28.639 --> 00:34:30.279
And when they didn't pay?

413
00:34:32.159 --> 00:34:34.319
People in the neighbourhood
got word of it.

414
00:34:34.840 --> 00:34:38.239
Fear of gossip is the best way
to get your money back.

415
00:34:38.360 --> 00:34:41.439
What was Calise's percentage?
Did she send money to anybody?

416
00:34:41.560 --> 00:34:45.158
I don't know. Inspector.
But she was always alone.

417
00:34:45.840 --> 00:34:47.839
She never even
went back to her village.

418
00:34:47.960 --> 00:34:51.359
A niece of hers came to visit her
once. but we never saw her again.

419
00:34:51.480 --> 00:34:54.039
- What did she do with the money?
- Don't know.

420
00:34:55.560 --> 00:34:57.239
But I know what I did:

421
00:34:59.560 --> 00:35:03.519
I saved it for my daughter Antonietta.
for when I won't be around anymore.

422
00:35:14.160 --> 00:35:17.919
I'm sure you can tell us the addresses
and the stories of all these people.

423
00:35:24.320 --> 00:35:25.359
Maione.

424
00:35:31.160 --> 00:35:35.559
While I go to Modo. you stay here
and have Nunzia tell you everything.

425
00:35:37.600 --> 00:35:40.159
The last ones to see Calise
must come to the station.

426
00:35:44.280 --> 00:35:45.439
After you.

427
00:35:56.920 --> 00:35:59.359
She died between
10pm and midnight.

428
00:36:00.920 --> 00:36:04.039
But the murderer just sped up
the course of nature because...

429
00:36:04.800 --> 00:36:06.399
she had a bad bone tumour.

430
00:36:06.520 --> 00:36:09.119
She had 6 to 8 months
left to live. at most.

431
00:36:09.560 --> 00:36:13.319
You think that's nothing?
Another spring. another summer...

432
00:36:14.520 --> 00:36:16.679
No one had a right
to take that away.

433
00:36:17.480 --> 00:36:19.759
I absolutely agree with you.
my friend.

434
00:36:20.200 --> 00:36:22.679
You know.
dying from kicks and punches...

435
00:36:23.280 --> 00:36:24.999
Although she didn't feel them.

436
00:36:25.160 --> 00:36:27.519
She died from the first blow
from a blunt object.

437
00:36:28.600 --> 00:36:33.039
Given the force used. I think it was
a man or an angry young woman.

438
00:36:41.160 --> 00:36:43.439
NAPLES POLICE STATION

439
00:36:45.480 --> 00:36:46.480
KNOCK ON DOOR

440
00:36:47.680 --> 00:36:48.799
Inspector.

441
00:36:49.800 --> 00:36:52.799
Now we know
half of Sanita's business.

442
00:36:52.920 --> 00:36:54.839
We could be
fortune tellers ourselves.

443
00:36:55.520 --> 00:36:57.679
On my way back.
I called two of them in.

444
00:36:58.360 --> 00:37:00.199
One is Passarelli.
who's outside.

445
00:37:01.440 --> 00:37:03.399
A hilarious story.
you'll hear it later.

446
00:37:03.520 --> 00:37:07.599
The other is Colombo. She assured me
she'd be here as soon as possible.

447
00:37:07.720 --> 00:37:11.199
and she said she'd only been to Calise
once for a relationship problem.

448
00:37:11.400 --> 00:37:13.879
- And the others?
- Well. the others...

449
00:37:15.040 --> 00:37:18.079
I went to Ridolfi.
but he's got a broken leg

450
00:37:18.200 --> 00:37:20.199
and would never
have made it to Calise.

451
00:37:20.880 --> 00:37:25.439
The last one of the day was a debtor.
and in fact it just says; "pay".

452
00:37:25.760 --> 00:37:29.199
That's Antonio lodice.
known as Tonino. a pizza chef.

453
00:37:29.320 --> 00:37:32.599
I wanted to go there. but then I sent
Cesarano and Camarda to call him.

454
00:37:32.720 --> 00:37:34.799
. Tonino. the guy
who. sells pizza from his cart?

455
00:37:34.920 --> 00:37:38.999
Exactly. Tonino. He sold the cart
because he opened a restaurant.

456
00:37:39.120 --> 00:37:43.319
' He asked for a loan.
but he's in debt up to his neck.

457
00:37:44.400 --> 00:37:45.919
And this Emma?

458
00:37:46.360 --> 00:37:50.159
Emma Serra d'Arpaja.
she's Calise's most regular client.

459
00:37:50.840 --> 00:37:53.399
But strangely.
Petrone knew almost nothing.

460
00:37:53.560 --> 00:37:56.559
because apparently.
Calise never asked her to follow her.

461
00:37:56.880 --> 00:37:58.919
Maybe because she knew her.

462
00:37:59.280 --> 00:38:03.879
It's strange. Emma Serra d'Arpaja
is an important woman

463
00:38:04.000 --> 00:38:06.719
- from the Santa Lucia neighbourhood.
- Have you called her in?

464
00:38:07.840 --> 00:38:11.959
It's better you go in person rather
than sending officers to her house.

465
00:38:12.640 --> 00:38:15.639
If Garzo finds out
we've bothered someone important...

466
00:38:15.760 --> 00:38:17.879
You know that
to make Garzo happy.

467
00:38:18.000 --> 00:38:20.519
we should erase
the Santa Lucia lady from the list.

468
00:38:20.640 --> 00:38:23.479
so we might as well send
Camarda and Cesarano to her too.

469
00:38:23.640 --> 00:38:26.319
- Let Passarelli in. we'll get started.
- Certainly.

470
00:38:27.000 --> 00:38:29.199
Passarelli. come in.

471
00:38:30.280 --> 00:38:32.919
No. Inspector.
To be honest. nothing new.

472
00:38:33.680 --> 00:38:38.079
- And in fact. nothing happened.
- Why. what was supposed to happen?

473
00:38:38.400 --> 00:38:39.999
Go on. Passarelli.

474
00:38:40.120 --> 00:38:43.919
tell the Inspector
why you went to see her.

475
00:38:44.480 --> 00:38:46.919
You see. Inspector.
I still live with my mother.

476
00:38:47.760 --> 00:38:49.879
She's a good woman.
don't get me wrong.

477
00:38:50.000 --> 00:38:54.679
But she's old now. she's sick
and a bit sharp-tempered.

478
00:38:55.560 --> 00:38:57.399
What's this got to do
with Calise?

479
00:38:57.520 --> 00:39:01.559
The thing is. I'm a methodical person.
I like to be organised.

480
00:39:02.400 --> 00:39:05.439
So it'd be helpful for me
to know more or less

481
00:39:05.560 --> 00:39:08.439
when my mother will leave us.

482
00:39:09.400 --> 00:39:11.799
So my fiancee and I
can get married.

483
00:39:12.040 --> 00:39:14.199
Inspector. Mother never
wanted me to marry!

484
00:39:15.000 --> 00:39:18.559
- How long have you been engaged?
- We were young.

485
00:39:19.160 --> 00:39:22.919
Not that we're in a hurry.
With everything that needs doing!

486
00:39:23.040 --> 00:39:26.319
- You know. the ceremony. the dowry...

487
00:39:26.640 --> 00:39:29.559
Not to mention
the house. the furniture...

488
00:39:30.200 --> 00:39:33.479
Besides. Inspector.
we have to prepare the kids' room.

489
00:39:34.760 --> 00:39:37.559
- So you've got children.
- Not yet. no.

490
00:39:37.680 --> 00:39:39.999
But my fiancee likes
big families.

491
00:39:40.280 --> 00:39:44.199
I see. Sorry. Passarelli.
how old is your fiancee?

492
00:39:44.320 --> 00:39:47.919
60. Just 2 years older than me.
But she looks much younger. Inspector.

493
00:39:49.400 --> 00:39:51.119
That woman was amazing!

494
00:39:51.680 --> 00:39:54.839
She told me the exact same things
as the doctor. a day earlier.

495
00:39:55.360 --> 00:39:57.119
All right. Passarelli.
you can go.

496
00:39:58.040 --> 00:39:59.399
- Goodbye.
- Goodbye.

497
00:39:59.520 --> 00:40:02.039
- Our best to your fiancee.
- Raffaele...

498
00:40:03.360 --> 00:40:05.399
Go and see
if Colombo's arrived yet.

499
00:40:09.480 --> 00:40:10.480
KNOCK ON DOOR

500
00:40:11.160 --> 00:40:12.599
- Who is it?
- Giuseppe.

501
00:40:12.720 --> 00:40:13.720
Yes.

502
00:40:17.600 --> 00:40:19.519
- Morning. Giuseppe.
- Morning. Teresa.

503
00:40:19.640 --> 00:40:20.719
Come in.

504
00:40:22.640 --> 00:40:23.919
What is it?

505
00:40:24.040 --> 00:40:27.159
- Two police officers are here. Teresa.

506
00:40:27.720 --> 00:40:30.399
- They gave me this letter.
- What is it?

507
00:40:30.800 --> 00:40:33.959
- A summons from the police station.
- The police station?

508
00:40:36.160 --> 00:40:37.199
Good morning. sir.

509
00:40:37.520 --> 00:40:39.959
- What summons?
- It’s for your wife.

510
00:40:40.200 --> 00:40:42.359
- My wife?
- That's what they said.

511
00:40:52.400 --> 00:40:54.759
- Goodbye. Teresa.
- No. wait. Giuseppe.

512
00:40:55.480 --> 00:40:56.559
Come here.

513
00:40:58.160 --> 00:41:00.159
Could you tell me
what this says?

514
00:41:00.560 --> 00:41:01.919
I can't read.

515
00:41:03.560 --> 00:41:05.359
You don't know what happened?

516
00:41:06.120 --> 00:41:08.559
The fortune teller from Sanita
was killed.

517
00:41:09.360 --> 00:41:10.999
Have a nice day. Teresa.

518
00:41:12.880 --> 00:41:14.159
Good day.

519
00:41:16.640 --> 00:41:18.999
WOMAN DEAD IN SANITA

520
00:41:20.240 --> 00:41:22.679
- Please come in. miss.
- Thank you. Sergeant.

521
00:41:35.200 --> 00:41:36.200
HE CLEARS HIS THROAT

522
00:41:43.720 --> 00:41:45.279
Have a seat.

523
00:41:48.720 --> 00:41:52.639
Miss. have a seat. Inspector Ricciardi
has to ask you some questions.

524
00:41:53.160 --> 00:41:54.160
Please.

525
00:42:18.920 --> 00:42:23.079
Are you Miss Enrica Colombo?

526
00:42:23.480 --> 00:42:26.479
103. Santa Teresa
degli Scalzi Street. Is that you?

527
00:42:26.720 --> 00:42:29.399
Sergeant.
you handed me the summons

528
00:42:29.520 --> 00:42:31.439
and I signed the receipt.
so yes. it's me.

529
00:42:34.040 --> 00:42:36.879
Well. then maybe
you know Mrs Calise.

530
00:42:37.000 --> 00:42:40.599
Carmela Calise. a fortune teller?

531
00:42:42.000 --> 00:42:43.039
Yes.

532
00:42:43.720 --> 00:42:46.599
I heard about her death.
I saw her the day before it happened.

533
00:42:46.720 --> 00:42:48.759
- Is that not allowed?
- Of course it is.

534
00:42:48.880 --> 00:42:52.919
We just want to know if you noticed
anything strange. unusual.

535
00:42:53.040 --> 00:42:55.199
Sergeant.
I only went there once.

536
00:42:55.480 --> 00:42:58.039
I don't know
what Mrs Calise was like usually.

537
00:43:01.000 --> 00:43:04.479
Then maybe you saw
someone coming in or out.

538
00:43:04.600 --> 00:43:06.759
- someone who caught your eye.
- No.

539
00:43:07.520 --> 00:43:09.199
Just a nosy caretaker.

540
00:43:09.320 --> 00:43:11.479
Now if that's all.
if I may. I'd like to go.

541
00:43:17.280 --> 00:43:19.759
- Go ahead.
- Goodbye.

542
00:43:20.320 --> 00:43:21.320
Miss.

543
00:43:24.520 --> 00:43:26.239
I need to ask you
something. please.

544
00:43:28.240 --> 00:43:30.159
What did you ask Mrs Calise?

545
00:43:31.440 --> 00:43:33.279
What did you want
to know from her?

546
00:43:35.520 --> 00:43:37.759
I don't think
I have to tell you that. Good day.

547
00:43:44.440 --> 00:43:46.879
- Did I say something wrong?
- Nothing. Inspector.

548
00:43:47.000 --> 00:43:49.039
You didn’t say a word.

549
00:43:54.000 --> 00:43:56.439
I'm so stupid. I'm so stupid!

550
00:44:13.920 --> 00:44:15.159
What was that?

551
00:45:01.120 --> 00:45:03.439
Tonino. what's that face for?

552
00:45:04.400 --> 00:45:06.679
You seemed happier
when you had your cart.

553
00:45:07.400 --> 00:45:10.119
- Was it worth it?
- Never mind. it's complicated.

554
00:45:10.880 --> 00:45:13.399
- Is the pizza good?
- Delicious.

555
00:45:14.160 --> 00:45:16.359
The important thing is
that customers are happy

556
00:45:16.560 --> 00:45:18.119
so they bring other customers.

557
00:45:20.640 --> 00:45:21.799
Time flies.

558
00:45:33.880 --> 00:45:36.679
- Are you here to eat?
- Chance would be a fine thing.

559
00:45:36.960 --> 00:45:39.679
We're looking for
Mr Antonio lodice.

560
00:45:47.360 --> 00:45:49.160
SHE SCREAMS. HE SCREAMS

561
00:45:50.160 --> 00:45:52.279
- Tonino!
- What have you done?

562
00:45:52.480 --> 00:45:54.439
Tonino! Tonino. my God!

563
00:45:54.640 --> 00:45:56.399
Oh my God!

564
00:45:56.880 --> 00:45:59.399
- What have you done?
- Move out of the way!

565
00:45:59.600 --> 00:46:01.959
- Dad!
- Move out of the way.

566
00:46:03.120 --> 00:46:04.879
Let us get to him!

567
00:46:07.720 --> 00:46:09.839
He's breathing.
Grab that table. hurry up.

568
00:46:10.640 --> 00:46:13.159
Come on. grab his feet.
Let's put him on the table.

569
00:46:20.960 --> 00:46:22.919
- Get out!
- Show's over.

570
00:46:23.040 --> 00:46:25.919
- Go away. there's nothing to see.
- Move it! Come on!

571
00:46:26.040 --> 00:46:29.559
Inspector. he knows
you're still investigating.

572
00:46:29.760 --> 00:46:31.879
but he wants you
to stop by his office.

573
00:46:32.000 --> 00:46:36.159
See? As you said. Serra d'Arpaja
must have been summoned.

574
00:46:36.560 --> 00:46:40.639
- Let's hear Garzo's complaints.
- Thank you. Inspector. Thank you.

575
00:46:40.760 --> 00:46:41.919
Get your eyes checked.

576
00:46:42.040 --> 00:46:45.759
- There's something wrong with them.
- No. nothing wrong with them...

577
00:46:45.880 --> 00:46:47.359
It’s just me. I'm shy.

578
00:46:47.480 --> 00:46:50.239
Inspector. it's Camarda.
Someone's seriously injured.

579
00:46:50.360 --> 00:46:52.239
A pizza chef
who stabbed himself.

580
00:46:54.160 --> 00:46:55.999
I've just informed the Inspector.

581
00:46:56.120 --> 00:46:59.159
No. Inspector.
No. this way. Inspector.

582
00:46:59.280 --> 00:47:02.599
The pizza chef who...?
Do me a favour!

583
00:47:12.520 --> 00:47:14.439
Let's hope
Modo can operate on him.

584
00:47:15.520 --> 00:47:16.679
The Inspector.

585
00:47:17.480 --> 00:47:19.799
Inspector. we’re sorry.
but we had no idea.

586
00:47:20.120 --> 00:47:23.279
It's not your fault.
You did your best to save him.

587
00:47:23.680 --> 00:47:26.519
- Have you informed the family?
- His wife was there too.

588
00:47:26.640 --> 00:47:29.919
She came with-us.
That young woman there.

589
00:47:30.640 --> 00:47:32.399
And that should be
lodice's mother.

590
00:47:33.000 --> 00:47:36.119
We told them to wait.
Modo is operating on him.

591
00:47:41.960 --> 00:47:42.960
HE KNOCKS

592
00:47:43.240 --> 00:47:44.359
May I?

593
00:47:48.720 --> 00:47:49.799
Enrica.

594
00:47:51.080 --> 00:47:52.279
How are you?

595
00:47:55.680 --> 00:47:59.519
I was worried. I thought you'd come
and tell me what the police wanted.

596
00:48:00.520 --> 00:48:01.999
Sorry. Dad.

597
00:48:03.400 --> 00:48:05.599
Did they ask you
about the Blackshirts?

598
00:48:06.360 --> 00:48:07.559
Did they scare you?

599
00:48:07.920 --> 00:48:12.639
No. it was about a poor lady
that was killed. in Sanita.

600
00:48:13.240 --> 00:48:14.759
What have you got to do with it?

601
00:48:17.200 --> 00:48:20.079
You see.
she was a fortune teller.

602
00:48:21.800 --> 00:48:24.759
I went to her once
and had her read my cards.

603
00:48:26.240 --> 00:48:27.439
Your cards?

604
00:48:29.120 --> 00:48:32.399
Why. is something worrying you?
Something you want to know?

605
00:48:33.160 --> 00:48:35.239
Dad. please.
you're embarrassing me.

606
00:48:39.360 --> 00:48:42.959
Then why are you so sad?
Why are you locked in your room?

607
00:48:52.400 --> 00:48:55.199
Because during the conversation
at the police station.

608
00:48:55.320 --> 00:48:58.879
I came across
as unpleasant and patronising.

609
00:48:59.720 --> 00:49:01.559
just because I was embarrassed.

610
00:49:02.520 --> 00:49:04.199
I'm a horrible person.

611
00:49:06.680 --> 00:49:08.759
Never find anyone to love me!

612
00:49:09.960 --> 00:49:11.999
Because of
this ugly character of mine.

613
00:49:13.360 --> 00:49:16.439
Because even if a man wanted
to get to know me.

614
00:49:16.560 --> 00:49:18.359
he'd back away immediately.

615
00:49:18.560 --> 00:49:21.639
without ever showing his face again.
And he'd be right.

616
00:49:22.960 --> 00:49:26.359
Enrica. you haven’t got
an ugly character.

617
00:49:28.120 --> 00:49:29.439
You've got character.

618
00:49:30.720 --> 00:49:33.199
and the man who loves you
will appreciate that.

619
00:49:35.840 --> 00:49:38.840
BABY CRIES. WOMAN SINGS SOFTLY

620
00:49:45.600 --> 00:49:49.479
- It's late. Raffaele. go home.
- I'm not leaving you alone. Inspector.

621
00:49:50.880 --> 00:49:52.839
Think about your family.
not me. Go.

622
00:49:55.680 --> 00:49:57.519
Inspector. I have to ask you.

623
00:49:59.080 --> 00:50:02.839
because of how much I care about you.
You know I've been devoted to you...

624
00:50:06.440 --> 00:50:08.879
since Lucia and I stopped living.

625
00:50:11.320 --> 00:50:12.679
I'm worried.

626
00:50:13.640 --> 00:50:15.159
The way you look...

627
00:50:17.240 --> 00:50:19.519
It seems like
you've stopped living too.

628
00:50:21.680 --> 00:50:22.879
Luca!

629
00:50:24.160 --> 00:50:25.399
Luca!

630
00:50:25.800 --> 00:50:27.439
You've killed him!

631
00:50:27.560 --> 00:50:29.999
- Luca!
- Sergeant! Sergeant.

632
00:50:33.720 --> 00:50:35.599
I know he was your son.

633
00:50:36.400 --> 00:50:37.400
My condolences.

634
00:50:37.960 --> 00:50:41.279
If I may. I'd like to go in first.
by myself.

635
00:51:18.280 --> 00:51:20.399
I'm sorry. Dad. my old paunch.

636
00:51:22.680 --> 00:51:26.119
I'm sorry. Dad. my old paunch.

637
00:51:29.480 --> 00:51:31.999
I'm sorry. Dad. my old paunch.

638
00:51:35.200 --> 00:51:37.999
I'm sorry. Dad. my old paunch.

639
00:51:39.680 --> 00:51:42.759
I'm sorry. Dad. my old paunch.

640
00:51:43.880 --> 00:51:47.279
I'm sorry. Dad. my old paunch.

641
00:51:48.600 --> 00:51:50.399
Gentlemen. please stay back.

642
00:51:53.280 --> 00:51:54.479
Gentlemen.

643
00:52:01.000 --> 00:52:05.039
He loved you. Maione.
His last thought was for you.

644
00:52:07.120 --> 00:52:08.679
"Paunchy."

645
00:52:21.400 --> 00:52:22.999
How do you know that?

646
00:52:27.680 --> 00:52:29.199
That's what he called me.

647
00:52:36.080 --> 00:52:38.080
HE SOBS

648
00:52:41.080 --> 00:52:44.159
Raffaele.
you haven't stopped living.

649
00:52:45.080 --> 00:52:46.359
You can't.

650
00:52:47.680 --> 00:52:50.799
For your other children.
for your wife.

651
00:52:52.320 --> 00:52:56.159
Until Lucia can deal with it. you have
to deal with it for both of you.

652
00:52:58.480 --> 00:52:59.639
As for me.

653
00:53:02.760 --> 00:53:04.559
I never started living.

654
00:53:19.480 --> 00:53:21.560
He's lost a lot of blood.
I'm not sure he'll make it.

655
00:53:22.320 --> 00:53:26.319
He's sedated now and he needs
to stay under for the next 24 hours.

656
00:53:26.680 --> 00:53:29.519
Then you can talk to him.
if he survives.

657
00:53:32.240 --> 00:53:33.599
I'll wait for you outside.

658
00:53:43.800 --> 00:53:45.199
Is there any news?

659
00:53:45.920 --> 00:53:50.039
Madam. you should go home now.
for your children.

660
00:53:50.720 --> 00:53:55.079
The doctor who operated is the very best.
You couldn't ask for more.

661
00:53:56.560 --> 00:53:58.759
Now we just need to
wait and hope.

662
00:54:00.200 --> 00:54:01.399
Thank you.

663
00:54:04.200 --> 00:54:05.840
SHE SOBS

664
00:54:13.160 --> 00:54:15.959
Let's hope
lodice can tell us something.

665
00:54:16.320 --> 00:54:18.159
It was like confessing.
wasn't it?

666
00:54:18.520 --> 00:54:21.319
Why would he kill himself
when he saw the police?

667
00:54:21.440 --> 00:54:25.079
No. Raffaele. That way of thinking
could come from anyone but you.

668
00:54:25.520 --> 00:54:28.559
Lodice had reasons to be desperate.
that's beyond doubt.

669
00:54:29.120 --> 00:54:32.079
But that doesn't necessarily mean
he killed Calise.

670
00:54:32.200 --> 00:54:35.279
- even if he was in debt.
- You're right. Inspector. I'm sorry.

671
00:54:37.120 --> 00:54:38.399
Now what?

672
00:54:38.880 --> 00:54:40.799
I have to take Modo out
for dinner. Join us?

673
00:54:40.920 --> 00:54:42.919
No. I should get going.

674
00:54:48.000 --> 00:54:49.240
SHE SIGHS

675
00:54:49.280 --> 00:54:50.520
KNOCK ON DOOR

676
00:54:50.840 --> 00:54:52.279
Who's that now? Yes?

677
00:54:52.880 --> 00:54:55.679
- Sergeant. good evening.
- Good evening. Filomena.

678
00:54:55.800 --> 00:54:59.319
- Come in.
- Came by to see how you are.

679
00:54:59.440 --> 00:55:01.239
I'm fine. thank God.

680
00:55:02.360 --> 00:55:03.399
My son. Gaetano.

681
00:55:03.640 --> 00:55:05.000
- Good evening.
- Nice to meet you.

682
00:55:05.960 --> 00:55:08.879
- Will you join us?
- Don't want to disturb you.

683
00:55:09.120 --> 00:55:11.759
- Made Genovese pasta.
- Can smell it.

684
00:55:11.880 --> 00:55:15.279
Yeah. I know.
The smell gets in your clothes.

685
00:55:15.400 --> 00:55:18.919
- Does it bother you?
- Go mad for Genovese pasta.

686
00:55:20.040 --> 00:55:23.039
Then have a seat.
I've got a plate ready for you.

687
00:55:26.960 --> 00:55:28.960
HE LAUGHS

688
00:55:33.680 --> 00:55:35.680
Mmm. ah.

689
00:55:36.800 --> 00:55:39.439
Smell that..
Can you smell it. Ricciardi?

690
00:55:40.880 --> 00:55:45.279
Don't listen. Can't you smell that
spring is here? Aren't you happy?

691
00:55:45.760 --> 00:55:48.519
A man just stabbed himself
and a woman's dead.

692
00:55:48.640 --> 00:55:50.039
If this is spring. it's all yours.

693
00:55:50.160 --> 00:55:52.919
What does people's madness
have to do with the seasons?

694
00:55:53.040 --> 00:55:55.399
Look who governs us
during all four seasons!

695
00:55:56.840 --> 00:56:00.719
One day I'll find an order on my desk
to arrest you and send you to the border.

696
00:56:01.640 --> 00:56:05.199
Just laugh it off. You know what I do
so people know I'm not a Fascist?

697
00:56:05.320 --> 00:56:07.719
I refuse to prescribe
purge medicines now!

698
00:56:08.880 --> 00:56:10.399
You never know.

699
00:56:11.560 --> 00:56:13.719
Let's have another glass
of this good wine.

700
00:56:14.240 --> 00:56:16.319
Or are you in a hurry
to get home?

701
00:56:16.600 --> 00:56:18.679
The later I get home tonight.
the better.

702
00:56:19.720 --> 00:56:21.759
Did you make Nanny Rosa angry?

703
00:56:23.800 --> 00:56:24.959
Close.

704
00:56:25.920 --> 00:56:28.839
I made someone angry.
but not Rosa.

705
00:56:29.920 --> 00:56:31.879
A man or a woman?

706
00:56:33.200 --> 00:56:35.279
You made a woman angry.
Ricciardi?

707
00:56:35.640 --> 00:56:37.679
Yes.
A neighbour. yes.

708
00:56:40.280 --> 00:56:42.439
I had to interrogate. her
about the case.

709
00:56:43.640 --> 00:56:45.719
I was rude. awkward.

710
00:56:46.800 --> 00:56:49.399
I don't want.
to run into her again.

711
00:56:49.680 --> 00:56:53.279
Why not? It'd be your chance
to say you're sorry.

712
00:56:53.400 --> 00:56:56.359
Unless she's an old witch.
in which case. I agree with you.

713
00:56:56.960 --> 00:56:58.199
What's she like?

714
00:56:59.240 --> 00:57:01.439
Order dessert. I'm paying.

715
00:57:02.480 --> 00:57:04.279
- Tell me. doctor.
- Marchie.

716
00:57:04.640 --> 00:57:06.839
Bring us...
Do you want a baba?

717
00:57:08.360 --> 00:57:09.360
Two babas.

718
00:57:09.440 --> 00:57:12.199
- See you liked it.
- It was great.

719
00:57:13.040 --> 00:57:14.079
Well..

720
00:57:15.200 --> 00:57:17.199
Excuse me. but I'm going to bed.

721
00:57:17.400 --> 00:57:18.759
- Good night.
- Good night.

722
00:57:19.120 --> 00:57:21.199
- Give Mum a kiss.
- Good night. Mum.

723
00:57:26.840 --> 00:57:28.679
My wife used
to do the same thing.

724
00:57:33.320 --> 00:57:36.999
She used to?
Your wife is gone too?

725
00:57:37.920 --> 00:57:39.999
No. I mean. she's still here.

726
00:57:40.800 --> 00:57:42.279
But you're right.

727
00:57:43.800 --> 00:57:45.279
It's as if she were gone.

728
00:57:51.800 --> 00:57:53.919
My firstborn son.

729
00:57:57.960 --> 00:57:59.759
was a policeman like me.

730
00:58:02.920 --> 00:58:04.199
And he was killed.

731
00:58:05.040 --> 00:58:06.159
Oh no!

732
00:58:08.440 --> 00:58:09.559
I'm sorry.

733
00:58:10.360 --> 00:58:13.359
I'm sorry to share this with you.
it's just I really feel...

734
00:58:14.400 --> 00:58:17.279
as if I've known you
for a long time.

735
00:58:18.080 --> 00:58:21.279
- But perhaps I shouldn't...
- No. no. Raffaele.

736
00:58:22.040 --> 00:58:23.999
You can tell me anything.

737
00:58:26.320 --> 00:58:29.439
My wife can barely talk.

738
00:58:30.800 --> 00:58:32.239
can barely breathe.

739
00:58:33.800 --> 00:58:35.199
And neither can I.

740
00:58:37.000 --> 00:58:39.079
I can't get over the pain.

741
00:58:40.640 --> 00:58:44.519
But we've got four children
and life has to go on. right?

742
00:58:46.280 --> 00:58:48.199
But in the Maione household.

743
00:58:50.440 --> 00:58:51.879
time stands still.

744
00:59:27.720 --> 00:59:30.559
No... Tonino. no!

745
00:59:31.720 --> 00:59:33.559
Dad. Dad!

746
00:59:35.000 --> 00:59:37.000
SHE SNIFFS

747
00:59:38.680 --> 00:59:40.680
SHE SNIFFS AGAIN

748
01:00:29.080 --> 01:00:30.959
You're not having
your coffee substitute?

749
01:00:32.440 --> 01:00:34.639
Of course I'll drink some.

750
01:00:35.560 --> 01:00:38.039
When have I ever not drunk it?

751
01:00:38.240 --> 01:00:40.519
You didn't even look at
last night's dinner.

752
01:00:40.800 --> 01:00:42.319
I got home late.

753
01:00:42.560 --> 01:00:45.359
Since when does getting home late
make you-not hungry?

754
01:00:46.400 --> 01:00:48.559
I had a little snack
at the station.

755
01:00:49.600 --> 01:00:53.119
Careful. -Raffaele. You'll destroy
your health with all these snacks.

756
01:01:00.440 --> 01:01:02.479
Goodness. Inspector.
I'm so sorry.

757
01:01:03.520 --> 01:01:06.239
Not just for the investigation.
for those poor women too.

758
01:01:06.560 --> 01:01:07.799
So am I.

759
01:01:08.200 --> 01:01:09.200
KNOCK ON DOOR

760
01:01:09.520 --> 01:01:10.919
Come in.

761
01:01:14.160 --> 01:01:17.239
Sergeant. may we come in?
We need to speak to the Inspector.

762
01:01:17.520 --> 01:01:19.079
Mrs lodice. have a seat.

763
01:01:20.040 --> 01:01:21.399
Tell me.

764
01:01:23.200 --> 01:01:25.039
You seem like
a good person to me.

765
01:01:26.160 --> 01:01:28.159
and I have to defend
my husband's name.

766
01:01:29.880 --> 01:01:31.839
So I want to tell you
everything I know.

767
01:01:33.360 --> 01:01:35.839
Believe me.
Tonino didn't kill anyone.

768
01:01:36.520 --> 01:01:39.679
Madam. we can only believe
the results of the investigation.

769
01:01:40.080 --> 01:01:42.999
but I can assure you
we'll proceed with the utmost care.

770
01:01:52.520 --> 01:01:55.879
It's lodice's promissory note.
It's bloodstained.

771
01:01:58.280 --> 01:02:01.799
I found it on him
the evening Calise was killed.

772
01:02:02.440 --> 01:02:05.199
I knew he'd been to see her.
even if he wouldn't tell me.

773
01:02:06.080 --> 01:02:08.759
So you knew he'd borrowed money?

774
01:02:11.120 --> 01:02:14.639
Our savings and the money
from selling the cart wasn't enough.

775
01:02:16.280 --> 01:02:18.719
Before opening the restaurant.
he was always smiling.

776
01:02:18.840 --> 01:02:22.719
then he stopped smiling.
Maybe that's why people didn't come.

777
01:02:23.120 --> 01:02:25.239
People don't eat
where people don't smile.

778
01:02:25.520 --> 01:02:27.879
But it wasn't him Inspector.
and you know that.

779
01:02:28.200 --> 01:02:30.999
He found her dead.
He took the promissory note and left.

780
01:02:31.120 --> 01:02:32.879
No. madam. I know nothing.

781
01:02:33.680 --> 01:02:35.759
But I'll do everything
to find out the truth.

782
01:02:36.600 --> 01:02:40.359
Thank you for coming to us.
But you need to know that.

783
01:02:41.160 --> 01:02:43.239
right now. your husband

784
01:02:44.200 --> 01:02:45.679
is the prime suspect.

785
01:02:57.760 --> 01:03:01.239
God is not a merchant
who pays on Saturday.

786
01:03:05.480 --> 01:03:07.599
Raffaele. what does that mean?

787
01:03:07.840 --> 01:03:10.279
It means sooner or later
you pay for what you do.

788
01:03:10.520 --> 01:03:13.199
Sorry. Inspector.
I forget you're not Neapolitan.

789
01:03:13.440 --> 01:03:17.319
It's an old Neapolitan proverb
which means that if you do something.

790
01:03:17.440 --> 01:03:21.119
God will punish or reward you
whenever he wants.

791
01:03:21.920 --> 01:03:25.319
There's no specific deadline.
like with men's debts.

792
01:03:25.440 --> 01:03:26.440
KNOCK ON DOOR

793
01:03:28.840 --> 01:03:32.159
Inspector. Deputy Garzo has arrived
and wants to see you immediately.

794
01:03:33.200 --> 01:03:35.479
- Raffaele. shall we?
- Don't know.

795
01:03:35.600 --> 01:03:38.639
- Sergeant. do me a favour. Come on.
- Let's do him a favour.

796
01:03:40.000 --> 01:03:41.439
- Follow me.
- Ponte...

797
01:03:41.840 --> 01:03:44.239
Go on. Ponte.
We know the way.

798
01:03:44.360 --> 01:03:46.839
- Go on.
- Thank you. Thank you.

799
01:03:47.240 --> 01:03:48.599
Certainly.

800
01:03:54.400 --> 01:03:55.400
Yes.

801
01:03:56.480 --> 01:03:57.839
Yes. yes.

802
01:03:59.440 --> 01:04:00.879
I'll be there.

803
01:04:03.720 --> 01:04:07.039
Well done. Ricciardi.
another quick success.

804
01:04:07.920 --> 01:04:10.799
Even in the age
of order and wellbeing.

805
01:04:10.920 --> 01:04:13.479
if madmen still exist
to create disorder.

806
01:04:13.600 --> 01:04:16.399
we're here to put things right.

807
01:04:17.800 --> 01:04:19.919
That's what I just heard
from Rome.

808
01:04:21.000 --> 01:04:23.359
I'm sorry. sir.
but the case is not closed.

809
01:04:27.720 --> 01:04:31.279
What do you mean?
This lodice. the murderer...

810
01:04:32.080 --> 01:04:33.399
It was him.

811
01:04:33.800 --> 01:04:37.959
His conscience got
the best of him. It's clear.

812
01:04:38.880 --> 01:04:41.439
He didn't confess.
We cannot be certain.

813
01:04:41.800 --> 01:04:44.199
Plus we still need
to continue our interrogations.

814
01:04:45.560 --> 01:04:46.999
Interrogations.

815
01:04:48.400 --> 01:04:51.599
I heard you summoned the wife
of Serra d'Arpaja. the lawyer.

816
01:04:52.480 --> 01:04:55.439
He phoned me.
He was worried.

817
01:04:56.240 --> 01:05:00.359
I would avoid friction.
especially considering the fact

818
01:05:00.480 --> 01:05:05.159
that dragging out the investigation
seems to be a formality.

819
01:05:05.800 --> 01:05:08.639
Sir. I thought it was our duty
to search for the truth.

820
01:05:09.120 --> 01:05:13.479
It'd be strange for the police
to cancel an interrogation.

821
01:05:13.600 --> 01:05:16.199
I'd be forced
to add it to my report. right?

822
01:05:18.000 --> 01:05:21.959
Do you think
I could block an investigation?

823
01:05:22.080 --> 01:05:25.079
I’m just trying to maintain
a level of discretion.

824
01:05:26.120 --> 01:05:30.599
So the woman in question won't come
down to the station. You'll go to her.

825
01:05:32.160 --> 01:05:35.159
By car. so people don't see you
approach on foot.

826
01:05:36.960 --> 01:05:38.039
By car.

827
01:05:45.520 --> 01:05:48.919
You know. I realised last night
you were smiling purely out of duty.

828
01:05:50.280 --> 01:05:54.079
What. not even a reception with
the Mussolinis can distract you now?

829
01:05:54.720 --> 01:05:57.759
I know Edda's in China. but...

830
01:05:59.000 --> 01:06:00.399
It's not about Edda.

831
01:06:01.200 --> 01:06:02.919
Although I really do miss her.

832
01:06:03.800 --> 01:06:05.999
It's just my mind is elsewhere.

833
01:06:07.520 --> 01:06:08.559
It’s normal. Livia.

834
01:06:11.240 --> 01:06:12.799
You've been widowed for a month.

835
01:06:15.640 --> 01:06:18.839
The truth is. I think it's time
to leave my old life behind me.

836
01:06:20.240 --> 01:06:21.759
with all its pain.

837
01:06:24.720 --> 01:06:27.159
You carry the death of a child
with you forever.

838
01:06:29.280 --> 01:06:32.759
But maybe with someone who's
sensitive enough to understand it.

839
01:06:33.800 --> 01:06:35.519
I could learn to live with it.

840
01:06:36.920 --> 01:06:38.839
- Start living again.
- Of course.

841
01:06:39.760 --> 01:06:44.239
You're young. beautiful. talented.
You have to start living again!

842
01:06:45.600 --> 01:06:48.599
Go on holiday. to a resort.

843
01:06:49.320 --> 01:06:52.679
And when you get back. you'll find
the. person you're looking for.

844
01:06:55.320 --> 01:06:57.159
- A resort?
- Yes.

845
01:07:15.400 --> 01:07:17.719
- Hello. The Serra d'Arpajas?
- Third floor.

846
01:07:26.160 --> 01:07:27.319
Thank you.

847
01:07:27.800 --> 01:07:31.639
Madam. let's talk about
your relationship with Mrs Calise.

848
01:07:31.960 --> 01:07:33.879
I know
you were a client of hers.

849
01:07:34.520 --> 01:07:35.999
I went there a few times.

850
01:07:38.840 --> 01:07:40.719
And what did you talk about?

851
01:07:40.960 --> 01:07:44.799
The dialogues between my wife and
Calise are not pertinent to the case.

852
01:07:44.920 --> 01:07:47.439
Sir. I permitted you to be here.

853
01:07:47.560 --> 01:07:51.399
but leave us to decide
what is pertinent and what is not.

854
01:07:54.680 --> 01:07:57.559
Answer. please. madam.
What did you talk about?

855
01:07:58.440 --> 01:08:00.679
Everything. I liked her.

856
01:08:01.880 --> 01:08:05.239
I didn't have to think.
She answered all my doubts.

857
01:08:05.560 --> 01:08:08.879
And lately.
have you been visiting her often?

858
01:08:09.080 --> 01:08:12.799
Inspector.
my wife said "a few times".

859
01:08:13.080 --> 01:08:15.679
It's an expression
that implies it was occasional.

860
01:08:15.960 --> 01:08:18.559
It does not mean "often".

861
01:08:22.440 --> 01:08:26.318
In this notebook.
Calise's appointment book.

862
01:08:27.200 --> 01:08:30.278
your wife's name appears
116 times in a year.

863
01:08:32.920 --> 01:08:35.519
I think it's fair to say "often".

864
01:08:35.920 --> 01:08:37.519
I used to go there. l-told you.

865
01:08:37.720 --> 01:08:40.318
Good. And since
you went there often.

866
01:08:41.080 --> 01:08:44.999
did Calise ever confide in you?
Did she mention anyone?

867
01:08:45.120 --> 01:08:46.999
Did she ever seem
worried about anything?

868
01:08:47.120 --> 01:08:49.759
No. Inspector.
She'd just read my cards.

869
01:08:51.600 --> 01:08:55.519
She told me what would happen.
and she was never wrong.

870
01:08:58.359 --> 01:08:59.439
Never.

871
01:09:02.760 --> 01:09:06.159
Raffaele. we need to dig deeper
into the lady's business.

872
01:09:06.480 --> 01:09:09.479
I don't understand why you didn't.
with all due respect.

873
01:09:09.600 --> 01:09:13.039
It was pointless. Her husband
was leading the interrogation.

874
01:09:13.160 --> 01:09:15.278
I understood
that the lady is unhappy.

875
01:09:15.560 --> 01:09:19.519
Couldn't she have started.
killing old ladies out of boredom?

876
01:09:20.359 --> 01:09:22.679
We know that she was
her most regular client

877
01:09:22.800 --> 01:09:25.839
and that Calise told her future
without ever being wrong.

878
01:09:26.319 --> 01:09:29.358
Even if she knew her well.
she must have had an informant.

879
01:09:30.760 --> 01:09:33.358
But we know
it wasn't Nunzia Petrone.

880
01:09:34.440 --> 01:09:35.639
Who. then?

881
01:09:38.000 --> 01:09:40.159
How about this?
I'll walk back.

882
01:09:40.520 --> 01:09:44.398
and you stay here to inquire
about Emma Serra d'Arpaja’s life.

883
01:09:44.520 --> 01:09:48.239
- Want to know everything about her.
- I'll buy the doorman a beer.

884
01:09:55.440 --> 01:09:57.759
- What a nice car!
- You can say that again.

885
01:09:57.880 --> 01:09:59.999
- This car's made history.
- Is it yours?

886
01:10:00.120 --> 01:10:01.359
I wish!

887
01:10:09.960 --> 01:10:12.519
You know you were
already dead on the ground.

888
01:10:13.480 --> 01:10:15.679
You know you were
already dead on the ground.

889
01:10:17.200 --> 01:10:19.639
You know you were
already dead on the ground.

890
01:10:22.200 --> 01:10:24.679
You know you were
already dead on the ground.

891
01:10:29.080 --> 01:10:32.039
Hi. Filomena.
Did you miss me?

892
01:10:33.520 --> 01:10:35.479
I had to go to Sorrento
for a few days.

893
01:10:35.600 --> 01:10:37.639
You know.
your Luigi is an important man.

894
01:10:38.120 --> 01:10:40.319
Important for whom?

895
01:10:40.920 --> 01:10:42.920
HE LAUGHS

896
01:10:43.360 --> 01:10:46.919
You know I love it when you're rude!
Let me in. your son's not home.

897
01:10:54.200 --> 01:10:55.559
Are you happy now?

898
01:10:58.440 --> 01:11:00.919
What? You don't want
to come in now?

899
01:11:14.960 --> 01:11:16.960
MUSIC PLAYS

900
01:11:19.120 --> 01:11:20.120
DOOR OPENS

901
01:11:23.600 --> 01:11:24.600
MUSIC STOPS

902
01:11:37.520 --> 01:11:39.679
Are you going to
get home late every night?

903
01:11:40.960 --> 01:11:44.399
You know that with an investigation
ongoing. there are no set hours.

904
01:11:45.880 --> 01:11:48.319
You used to let me know
when you'd be late.

905
01:11:48.640 --> 01:11:51.296
You'd send someone
from the station.

906
01:11:51.320 --> 01:11:54.439
or you'd call the lady on the 4th floor.
You'd always find a way.

907
01:11:55.760 --> 01:11:57.359
You're right. Before.

908
01:11:58.560 --> 01:12:01.399
- But before what?
- Again! Stop it.

909
01:12:01.960 --> 01:12:03.399
Before Luca died.

910
01:12:04.080 --> 01:12:06.119
There was a before
and there's an after.

911
01:12:06.240 --> 01:12:09.319
Our life used to be one way.
then it changed forever.

912
01:12:10.240 --> 01:12:12.199
But it's still life. Lucia.
Life!

913
01:12:12.560 --> 01:12:16.359
- And we have to live it.
- Oh. yeah? Then listen to me.

914
01:12:16.560 --> 01:12:19.999
The next time you're late
and don't tell me. you're dead. OK?

915
01:12:24.560 --> 01:12:26.879
Go and shower before you eat.

916
01:12:27.000 --> 01:12:29.759
You smell of beer.
At least it's not onions you smell of.

917
01:13:17.080 --> 01:13:19.879
It took three beers to make
the Serras' driver talk.

918
01:13:20.000 --> 01:13:23.479
but I got two very important
pieces of information.

919
01:13:23.600 --> 01:13:27.679
Which one first. Inspector?
- Don't know. Maione. You choose.

920
01:13:27.760 --> 01:13:30.919
I'll start with the juicier one.
then the more important one.

921
01:13:31.040 --> 01:13:34.679
The lady has a relationship
with a theatre actor.

922
01:13:34.840 --> 01:13:37.839
Everyone knows. The husband too.
according to the doorman.

923
01:13:38.160 --> 01:13:40.879
But he says nothing.
The actor's in a variety show.

924
01:13:41.120 --> 01:13:43.959
She goes to see it
three or four times a week.

925
01:13:44.080 --> 01:13:47.519
Without her husband. obviously.
Or rather. she used to go.

926
01:13:47.760 --> 01:13:50.159
Apparently.
she hasn't been for a few days.

927
01:13:51.000 --> 01:13:53.719
You've got an even more important
piece of information?

928
01:13:53.840 --> 01:13:55.439
I should send you around
more often.

929
01:13:55.560 --> 01:13:59.439
I found out who Calise's informant
about Emma's personal life is.

930
01:13:59.800 --> 01:14:02.239
A female informant.

931
01:14:02.680 --> 01:14:03.959
Who is it?

932
01:14:04.080 --> 01:14:08.639
Inspector. there's a young lady
waiting for you in your office.

933
01:14:08.760 --> 01:14:10.959
- What young lady?
- Don't know her name.

934
01:14:11.080 --> 01:14:14.879
She said you met once
and she'll only speak to you.

935
01:14:15.000 --> 01:14:16.000
All right.

936
01:14:19.280 --> 01:14:20.799
Yes. I've just read it.

937
01:14:21.000 --> 01:14:22.319
Good morning. Inspector.

938
01:14:27.440 --> 01:14:28.759
- Inspector. it's her.
- No.

939
01:14:28.880 --> 01:14:30.399
I was about to tell you.

940
01:14:31.120 --> 01:14:33.759
Calise's informant. Serras' maid.

941
01:14:35.280 --> 01:14:38.879
The doorman says the lady here
took the tram to Calise every day.

942
01:14:39.040 --> 01:14:41.519
He knows because
he was the one to tell her

943
01:14:42.040 --> 01:14:43.879
which tram to take
the first time.

944
01:14:44.520 --> 01:14:48.399
Good morning. miss.
What did you want to talk to me about?

945
01:14:49.360 --> 01:14:51.359
My name is Teresa Scognamiglio.

946
01:14:52.680 --> 01:14:55.319
Carmela Calise was my aunt.

947
01:14:56.800 --> 01:14:58.199
on my mother's side.

948
01:14:59.120 --> 01:15:02.119
It took me a long time to come.
and I'm sure I'll lose my job.

949
01:15:02.240 --> 01:15:03.799
but I couldn't
keep quiet anymore.

950
01:15:04.920 --> 01:15:09.759
These shoes belong to my master.
Mr Serra d'Arpaja.

951
01:15:10.400 --> 01:15:12.359
And my aunt's blood is on them.

952
01:15:14.000 --> 01:15:17.039
In my village. people said
terrible things about my aunt.

953
01:15:17.640 --> 01:15:20.199
because she left home
when she was still a spinster.

954
01:15:20.920 --> 01:15:23.999
I'd never met her. It all happened
when I was just a baby.

955
01:15:24.480 --> 01:15:27.959
When I came to Naples.
I looked her up. I was curious.

956
01:15:30.360 --> 01:15:31.999
All I had was an address.

957
01:15:38.840 --> 01:15:41.799
When I found her.
she told me all about the cards

958
01:15:41.920 --> 01:15:43.759
and how she could
read the future.

959
01:15:46.800 --> 01:15:49.759
She told you all about the scam
without even knowing you?

960
01:15:49.920 --> 01:15:51.399
She knew I admired her.

961
01:15:52.000 --> 01:15:55.399
She'd made a fortune taking
advantage of rich people's naivety.

962
01:15:55.520 --> 01:15:57.559
And that seemed incredible to me.

963
01:15:57.680 --> 01:16:00.599
So you told her
about Mrs Serra d'Arpaja.

964
01:16:02.640 --> 01:16:04.599
I told her where to meet her.

965
01:16:13.600 --> 01:16:16.519
My mistress told me
she'd met a fortune teller.

966
01:16:17.200 --> 01:16:19.959
I started telling my aunt
everything the lady did.

967
01:16:20.080 --> 01:16:22.999
then. at one point.
it was no longer necessary.

968
01:16:24.640 --> 01:16:27.279
My aunt gave me a little money
and I was happy.

969
01:16:28.040 --> 01:16:29.040
And her husband?

970
01:16:29.360 --> 01:16:32.599
Did he know
his wife was seeing a fortune teller?

971
01:16:33.280 --> 01:16:37.079
Yes. but he'd always pretend
he knew nothing. About the rest too.

972
01:16:37.280 --> 01:16:40.159
For example.
his wife's relationship with an actor.

973
01:16:40.920 --> 01:16:42.639
See. even you know about it!

974
01:16:43.640 --> 01:16:45.519
I don't know what happened next.

975
01:16:45.640 --> 01:16:48.759
She suddenly
became sad. desperate.

976
01:16:48.880 --> 01:16:50.239
Her room was a mess.

977
01:16:50.360 --> 01:16:53.199
vomit stains all over the place.
and there was...

978
01:16:53.360 --> 01:16:54.959
- Vomit?
- Yes.

979
01:16:56.040 --> 01:16:57.319
She drinks.

980
01:16:58.040 --> 01:16:59.519
Everything changed.

981
01:17:00.440 --> 01:17:02.639
Even her husband
has stopped pretending.

982
01:17:02.920 --> 01:17:05.399
One evening. I heard
the two of them fighting.

983
01:17:05.520 --> 01:17:07.919
He said if she didn't stop
seeing that old lady.

984
01:17:08.040 --> 01:17:10.359
he'd find a way to shut her up.

985
01:17:10.480 --> 01:17:12.039
WOMAN DEAD IN SANITA

986
01:17:12.640 --> 01:17:13.919
In fact..

987
01:17:16.800 --> 01:17:19.439
All right. miss.
That's a motive.

988
01:17:20.120 --> 01:17:22.599
But Mr Serra d'Arpaja says
that when Calise was killed.

989
01:17:22.720 --> 01:17:24.479
he was at dinner
at the prefect's.

990
01:17:24.600 --> 01:17:27.319
I don't know about that.
but I know what time he came home.

991
01:17:27.680 --> 01:17:30.679
It was late at night.
and he was dirty and dishevelled.

992
01:17:31.120 --> 01:17:35.199
When I saw him in the hallway. he said
not to tell anyone I'd seen him.

993
01:17:35.920 --> 01:17:37.919
He was wearing
these shoes. Inspector.

994
01:17:38.720 --> 01:17:40.359
Who's going to tell Garzo?

995
01:17:41.560 --> 01:17:43.399
It might not have been him.

996
01:17:43.720 --> 01:17:46.599
Sir. the maid even brought
his bloody shoes.

997
01:17:46.720 --> 01:17:49.679
But she didn't see
the Serra d'Arpaja kill Calise.

998
01:17:49.880 --> 01:17:53.959
A pair of dirty shoes
cannot prove a murder.

999
01:17:54.360 --> 01:17:57.839
It could be a dead dog's blood.

1000
01:18:00.040 --> 01:18:01.319
But there's a motive.

1001
01:18:01.840 --> 01:18:05.279
The dinner at the prefect's could have
been over by the time of the murder.

1002
01:18:07.960 --> 01:18:09.039
Listen.

1003
01:18:10.120 --> 01:18:13.839
We've got a servant who's accusing
a respectable man of law.

1004
01:18:14.480 --> 01:18:16.479
And we have a man in debt.

1005
01:18:16.600 --> 01:18:18.799
whose suicide
is basically a confession.

1006
01:18:19.880 --> 01:18:22.279
Who do you think
the court will believe?

1007
01:18:23.160 --> 01:18:24.519
That's true. sir.

1008
01:18:25.240 --> 01:18:27.039
So what do you intend to do?

1009
01:18:29.240 --> 01:18:30.399
Me?

1010
01:18:32.160 --> 01:18:33.559
What do I have to do with it?

1011
01:18:34.280 --> 01:18:37.559
It's your investigation. you have to
tell me what you intend to do.

1012
01:18:38.120 --> 01:18:39.399
You're right.

1013
01:18:40.040 --> 01:18:43.839
If I'm so insistent on verifying
Teresa Scognamiglio's statement.

1014
01:18:43.960 --> 01:18:47.039
it's to stop the police
from embarrassing ourselves.

1015
01:18:47.360 --> 01:18:49.639
I just need a few days
to investigate.

1016
01:18:50.400 --> 01:18:51.919
You have one day. Ricciardi.

1017
01:18:52.200 --> 01:18:55.999
I want someone charged
by tomorrow. clear?

1018
01:18:56.760 --> 01:18:57.959
Certainly.

1019
01:19:01.920 --> 01:19:05.319
How is it possible?
How can he be so dumb?

1020
01:19:05.800 --> 01:19:08.799
As if investigations
have a precise deadline!

1021
01:19:09.120 --> 01:19:12.079
And right now. when we could
finally clear lodice's name.

1022
01:19:12.360 --> 01:19:14.519
Garzo's right
about Serra d'Arpaja.

1023
01:19:14.760 --> 01:19:17.879
Those clues are useless in court
without evidence.

1024
01:19:18.520 --> 01:19:21.559
If we don't find any.
things will stay as they are.

1025
01:19:22.720 --> 01:19:25.719
At least we've got an extra day.
Let's try to make it count.

1026
01:19:29.880 --> 01:19:33.119
Have you ever thought about
everything you can see from a window?

1027
01:19:34.200 --> 01:19:35.999
You can see life. death.

1028
01:19:37.360 --> 01:19:39.119
Watching without intervening.

1029
01:19:41.520 --> 01:19:43.399
So who's the man who watches?

1030
01:19:44.840 --> 01:19:47.399
Not lodice. because he's dead.

1031
01:19:48.960 --> 01:19:51.719
Not Serra d'Arpaja.
because otherwise...

1032
01:19:54.040 --> 01:19:58.159
Sorry. Inspector. Maybe
I didn't understand what you mean.

1033
01:19:58.800 --> 01:20:00.559
The man who watches
doesn't live.

1034
01:20:01.480 --> 01:20:04.159
He can only watch
other people's lives unfurling

1035
01:20:04.280 --> 01:20:05.959
and live through them.

1036
01:20:08.320 --> 01:20:11.719
What can you take from the man
watching from the window?

1037
01:20:16.760 --> 01:20:17.999
The window.

1038
01:20:20.400 --> 01:20:21.919
Sorry. Inspector.

1039
01:20:23.000 --> 01:20:24.719
are you talking about yourself?

1040
01:20:31.600 --> 01:20:33.839
Get me the Serra d'Arpaja house.
please.

1041
01:22:03.360 --> 01:22:04.360
Miss?

1042
01:22:05.520 --> 01:22:06.759
You don't live here.

1043
01:22:09.400 --> 01:22:10.959
Aren't you Maria's daughter?

1044
01:22:12.280 --> 01:22:14.879
- Yes.
- Are you looking for someone?

1045
01:22:15.240 --> 01:22:17.719
No. I was just lost in thought.

1046
01:22:18.720 --> 01:22:21.839
- Was looking at the cart.
- It's pretty. isn't it?

1047
01:22:21.960 --> 01:22:22.960
Very!

1048
01:22:23.560 --> 01:22:24.560
Goodbye.

1049
01:22:30.480 --> 01:22:32.199
The cart..

1050
01:22:33.080 --> 01:22:36.679
I know your husband went
to Calise's the night she died.

1051
01:22:38.760 --> 01:22:40.439
Who told you
he went to Calise's?

1052
01:22:45.840 --> 01:22:47.079
We...

1053
01:22:48.520 --> 01:22:50.359
argued a while ago.

1054
01:22:51.760 --> 01:22:53.399
I told him
I wanted to leave him.

1055
01:22:55.600 --> 01:22:59.839
It's true I blamed the fortune teller.
but he doesn't have the guts.

1056
01:23:00.160 --> 01:23:03.559
Maybe he found the courage once
he realised he might lose you forever.

1057
01:23:04.920 --> 01:23:08.759
I know you have
another man. an actor.

1058
01:23:10.560 --> 01:23:11.719
Attilio.

1059
01:23:13.480 --> 01:23:14.879
I told him everything.

1060
01:23:16.920 --> 01:23:18.079
Even that I’m pregnant.

1061
01:23:19.200 --> 01:23:21.679
That's the only thing
Calise could not foresee.

1062
01:23:21.880 --> 01:23:25.559
- Had to tell her.
- Had to? Who forced you to?

1063
01:23:26.120 --> 01:23:28.079
Inspector. laugh if you like.

1064
01:23:28.960 --> 01:23:32.599
but I had to. because
only she could tell me what to do.

1065
01:23:33.480 --> 01:23:36.439
So Calise ordered you
to leave your husband?

1066
01:23:37.080 --> 01:23:38.639
No. that's the crazy thing.

1067
01:23:40.160 --> 01:23:42.239
She pushed me towards Attilio.

1068
01:23:42.360 --> 01:23:44.359
The cards said
we were destined for each other

1069
01:23:44.480 --> 01:23:46.159
and I should leave with him.

1070
01:23:48.040 --> 01:23:51.279
Everything was ready.
Money. documents.

1071
01:23:52.440 --> 01:23:54.079
is child in my worn

1072
01:23:55.400 --> 01:23:58.439
But then the cards said
I shouldn't ever see him again.

1073
01:23:59.200 --> 01:24:00.200
Why not?

1074
01:24:01.200 --> 01:24:04.199
Cards don't give reasons.
They show you the path.

1075
01:24:04.840 --> 01:24:06.359
So I did what I had to.

1076
01:24:07.480 --> 01:24:08.919
and I bid him farewell.

1077
01:24:09.480 --> 01:24:10.719
Does he know?

1078
01:24:11.520 --> 01:24:14.919
Does he know the cards brought you
together and then separated you?

1079
01:24:15.800 --> 01:24:19.079
No. Inspector.
I might be mad. but I'm not stupid.

1080
01:24:20.680 --> 01:24:25.919
I told myself so many time’s that
my behaviour might be absurd. childish.

1081
01:24:27.720 --> 01:24:30.839
But you must never show yourself
to be ridiculous to the man you love.

1082
01:24:33.600 --> 01:24:36.639
Now that Calise's gone and
she can no longer tell you what to do.

1083
01:24:37.080 --> 01:24:38.799
haven't you changed your mind?

1084
01:24:40.720 --> 01:24:41.759
Inspector.

1085
01:24:42.520 --> 01:24:45.959
the cards spoke through her.
but they're not her.

1086
01:24:46.800 --> 01:24:48.959
It's the souls of the dead
talking to you.

1087
01:24:49.280 --> 01:24:50.919
and if you don't listen to them.

1088
01:24:51.040 --> 01:24:53.759
terrible tragedy will befall you
and those you love.

1089
01:24:55.680 --> 01:24:57.919
Isn't it already
a terrible tragedy

1090
01:24:58.880 --> 01:25:00.359
to give up on love?

1091
01:25:03.840 --> 01:25:05.599
You're right. Inspector.

1092
01:25:08.360 --> 01:25:10.079
I wasn't afraid for myself.

1093
01:25:10.800 --> 01:25:12.079
but for my child.

1094
01:25:13.520 --> 01:25:15.719
Ever since it's been
inside of me. it's become...

1095
01:25:18.320 --> 01:25:20.559
the most important thing
I've ever had.

1096
01:25:22.080 --> 01:25:23.639
I gave it up for my baby.

1097
01:25:29.880 --> 01:25:32.959
Inspector. why didn't you tell her
that Calise was a swindler?

1098
01:25:33.080 --> 01:25:36.639
I don't know. Raffaele. I guess
because there's a child involved.

1099
01:25:37.320 --> 01:25:39.079
I want to be sure
about the murderer.

1100
01:25:39.200 --> 01:25:42.559
before telling her anything
that could send her spiralling.

1101
01:25:42.760 --> 01:25:46.079
- Still think it was the husband.
- Then let's find the evidence.

1102
01:25:46.960 --> 01:25:49.479
so she’ll have one more reason
to go back to her love

1103
01:25:49.600 --> 01:25:51.319
and live happily ever after.

1104
01:25:51.680 --> 01:25:55.039
Until then. we don't have the right
to decide her destiny.

1105
01:25:55.160 --> 01:25:57.719
Just as the cards and Calise.
God bless her soul. didn't.

1106
01:25:58.520 --> 01:26:02.279
You're right. But what can we do?
We don't have time.

1107
01:26:06.760 --> 01:26:09.760
PIANO MUSIC

1108
01:26:35.320 --> 01:26:38.879
- Chiara wait for the music to start!
- I'm sorry.

1109
01:26:39.480 --> 01:26:40.719
What's going on?

1110
01:26:41.480 --> 01:26:42.919
- Who are you?
- Police.

1111
01:26:43.040 --> 01:26:45.839
We're looking for
Mr Attilio Romor. the actor.

1112
01:26:46.000 --> 01:26:48.319
- Where can we find him?
- He's right here.

1113
01:26:49.240 --> 01:26:51.079
We rehearse every afternoon.

1114
01:26:51.840 --> 01:26:53.039
Attilio!
Yes?

1115
01:26:55.120 --> 01:26:57.879
- Has he done something?
- We just have some questions.

1116
01:26:58.720 --> 01:27:00.479
- Excuse me.
- Go ahead.

1117
01:27:01.360 --> 01:27:02.519
Hold this.

1118
01:27:03.880 --> 01:27:06.719
One. two. three and down...

1119
01:27:08.480 --> 01:27:11.359
For once. someone's looking for you
who's not in a skirt.

1120
01:27:13.480 --> 01:27:15.599
- Good evening. Mr Romor.
- Good evening.

1121
01:27:16.240 --> 01:27:19.039
This is Inspector Ricciardi.
I'm Sergeant Maione.

1122
01:27:19.440 --> 01:27:23.319
We have some questions about your
relationship with Mrs Serra d'Arpaja.

1123
01:27:23.680 --> 01:27:25.679
Why. has it become a crime?

1124
01:27:26.200 --> 01:27:29.719
We're investigating the murder
of a fortune teller the woman saw.

1125
01:27:30.840 --> 01:27:33.919
I didn't know
Emma saw a fortune teller.

1126
01:27:34.880 --> 01:27:38.399
It's true. we have a relationship.
We’re going to live together soon.

1127
01:27:39.320 --> 01:27:41.559
If you need to know
anything. just ask.

1128
01:27:42.960 --> 01:27:46.359
Actually. the lady mentioned
she'd told you that she was planning

1129
01:27:47.360 --> 01:27:48.759
not to see you anymore.

1130
01:27:49.600 --> 01:27:52.039
Sergeant. I know my Emma.

1131
01:27:52.520 --> 01:27:56.359
Faced with such an important decision.
it's natural she was a bit hesitant.

1132
01:27:57.680 --> 01:28:00.159
But I think it was her husband
who influenced her.

1133
01:28:00.720 --> 01:28:03.159
He even came to threaten me
and offered me money.

1134
01:28:03.720 --> 01:28:05.599
But I can't be bought.

1135
01:28:06.280 --> 01:28:10.199
Actually. I'm sure tonight Emma
will pick me up just as we agreed.

1136
01:28:10.760 --> 01:28:11.760
Tonight?

1137
01:28:12.760 --> 01:28:15.359
It's the last performance.
then we're leaving.

1138
01:28:43.680 --> 01:28:44.839
Inspector!

1139
01:28:45.160 --> 01:28:48.439
You were right. the lady had a car
ready to go to the theatre.

1140
01:28:49.080 --> 01:28:52.519
It's her last chance to see him.
I knew she couldn't resist.

1141
01:28:52.640 --> 01:28:55.319
Her husband also reserved
a box at the theatre.

1142
01:28:55.440 --> 01:28:56.759
unbeknownst to his wife.

1143
01:28:56.880 --> 01:28:59.279
Inspector. are we sure
he's not enjoying this

1144
01:28:59.400 --> 01:29:01.399
and wants a showdown?

1145
01:29:02.120 --> 01:29:03.759
Hopefully not.

1146
01:29:04.760 --> 01:29:06.719
In any case.
we're going to the theatre.

1147
01:29:06.840 --> 01:29:08.759
Prepare a plainclothes squad.

1148
01:29:09.040 --> 01:29:13.439
Go home. get changed and rest up.
because tonight we're going all in.

1149
01:29:13.880 --> 01:29:16.599
- We won't tell Garzo anything.
- Inspector. are you sure?

1150
01:29:16.720 --> 01:29:19.479
He was very clear about
not doing anything with the Serras.

1151
01:29:19.600 --> 01:29:23.719
If we tell him. he'll stop us.
We'll deal with him afterwards.

1152
01:29:24.400 --> 01:29:26.359
See you there.
I've got an idea.

1153
01:29:34.240 --> 01:29:35.240
KNOCK ON DOOR

1154
01:29:35.920 --> 01:29:36.999
Come in.

1155
01:29:39.760 --> 01:29:42.799
- Raffaele. good evening.
- Good evening. Filomena.

1156
01:29:43.000 --> 01:29:44.279
Come on in.

1157
01:29:46.720 --> 01:29:49.039
I need 5 minutes to talk to you.

1158
01:29:50.160 --> 01:29:51.279
Sure.

1159
01:29:59.320 --> 01:30:00.559
Filomena.

1160
01:30:01.520 --> 01:30:03.439
Over these past few days.

1161
01:30:04.840 --> 01:30:08.039
you've become a good friend.

1162
01:30:10.120 --> 01:30:11.439
But. you see...

1163
01:30:16.440 --> 01:30:17.959
I'm a policeman.

1164
01:30:19.400 --> 01:30:23.039
And I can't live knowing
that a crime has gone unsolved.

1165
01:30:24.520 --> 01:30:27.559
Whoever did this could come back.
with worse intentions.

1166
01:30:28.480 --> 01:30:29.599
Raffaele.

1167
01:30:30.760 --> 01:30:33.879
To me. you're something new.

1168
01:30:34.760 --> 01:30:37.359
Because you can see
the woman I really am.

1169
01:30:39.400 --> 01:30:40.919
You say we're friends.

1170
01:30:42.960 --> 01:30:45.479
but there are things
you can't even tell your friends.

1171
01:30:46.120 --> 01:30:47.479
Between friends..

1172
01:30:49.120 --> 01:30:50.479
A shadow like this?

1173
01:30:57.080 --> 01:30:58.199
Fine.

1174
01:30:58.760 --> 01:31:00.639
Then I'm talking to my friend.

1175
01:31:03.640 --> 01:31:07.199
But my friend has to promise me
that this won't leave the house.

1176
01:31:08.280 --> 01:31:09.639
I promise.

1177
01:31:13.280 --> 01:31:14.919
It was my son.

1178
01:31:19.040 --> 01:31:20.359
Why?

1179
01:31:23.240 --> 01:31:25.319
Because I've never been free.

1180
01:31:27.360 --> 01:31:29.159
Even when my husband was alive.

1181
01:31:30.160 --> 01:31:33.599
There was always someone trying
to lay a hand on me or gossiping.

1182
01:31:35.000 --> 01:31:37.519
Even more so
since I've been alone with Gaetano.

1183
01:31:39.280 --> 01:31:41.479
I really didn't know what to do.

1184
01:31:48.880 --> 01:31:50.719
Then one day. I remembered

1185
01:31:52.680 --> 01:31:54.279
when I was a child.

1186
01:31:57.880 --> 01:32:00.159
My father had a garden.

1187
01:32:01.760 --> 01:32:03.919
and there was a fox
in this garden.

1188
01:32:05.680 --> 01:32:07.999
So my father put out
a bunch of traps.

1189
01:32:10.320 --> 01:32:12.199
and one morning we woke up.

1190
01:32:14.240 --> 01:32:16.639
and you know
what we found inside a trap?

1191
01:32:22.040 --> 01:32:23.399
A paw.

1192
01:32:25.160 --> 01:32:28.319
The fox had ripped off its paw
to get back its freedom.

1193
01:32:31.400 --> 01:32:33.119
I had to do the same thing.

1194
01:32:34.960 --> 01:32:36.839
I had to rip off a paw.

1195
01:32:38.440 --> 01:32:40.919
because nobody wants
a deformed woman.

1196
01:32:44.040 --> 01:32:46.039
But I couldn't do it.
I was there.

1197
01:32:46.760 --> 01:32:49.759
with this knife in my hand.
and I was crying. crying.

1198
01:32:49.880 --> 01:32:51.319
Gaetano was crying too.

1199
01:32:53.760 --> 01:32:55.879
But then he took the knife

1200
01:32:57.720 --> 01:32:59.079
and he freed me.

1201
01:33:20.920 --> 01:33:22.759
Have you made Genovese pasta?

1202
01:33:36.400 --> 01:33:39.479
So you'll learn that
you can only eat onions at home.

1203
01:33:44.360 --> 01:33:46.039
What are you doing here
so early?

1204
01:33:47.080 --> 01:33:49.399
It's just that
I'm going to be home late tonight.

1205
01:33:51.000 --> 01:33:52.679
So I stopped by to tell you.

1206
01:33:58.400 --> 01:33:59.919
You're so beautiful. Lucia.

1207
01:34:03.040 --> 01:34:04.479
You're really beautiful.

1208
01:34:11.960 --> 01:34:13.319
You're my whole life.

1209
01:34:22.040 --> 01:34:23.879
You were right. Raffaele.

1210
01:34:24.760 --> 01:34:26.399
Spring is here.

1211
01:34:37.760 --> 01:34:41.159
- Thank you. madam. Come again.
- Goodbye.

1212
01:34:45.280 --> 01:34:47.439
Dad. if we're done here.
I'll go home.

1213
01:34:47.560 --> 01:34:48.799
Enrica. listen.

1214
01:34:50.920 --> 01:34:52.719
About what you were telling me...

1215
01:34:53.240 --> 01:34:57.279
I mean. that thing
about not finding love.

1216
01:34:58.760 --> 01:35:01.039
Were you referring
to anyone in particular?

1217
01:35:02.040 --> 01:35:05.319
Is that why you went
to that fortune teller?

1218
01:35:05.440 --> 01:35:08.479
- Dad. please.
- You can tell me. you know that.

1219
01:35:12.440 --> 01:35:14.959
No. don't worry. there's no one.

1220
01:35:17.040 --> 01:35:20.399
Besides. even if there were.
it’d be pointless talking about it.

1221
01:35:20.640 --> 01:35:21.640
No.

1222
01:35:22.640 --> 01:35:23.959
It's never pointless.

1223
01:35:25.480 --> 01:35:29.439
Our feelings are important.
Yours are important to me.

1224
01:35:29.960 --> 01:35:32.719
You can talk to me about it
whenever you want... Or not.

1225
01:35:33.440 --> 01:35:34.879
Up to you.

1226
01:35:35.680 --> 01:35:37.279
But if something is important.

1227
01:35:38.440 --> 01:35:39.999
don't let it get away.

1228
01:35:47.240 --> 01:35:50.119
Antonietta?
What do you need her for?

1229
01:35:50.760 --> 01:35:53.079
She was there
when they killed Calise.

1230
01:35:53.200 --> 01:35:55.959
You told me she stayed there.
even after you left.

1231
01:35:56.720 --> 01:36:00.479
Antonietta doesn't understand.
What do you want from that poor girl?

1232
01:36:00.600 --> 01:36:03.719
It's worth a shot. I "guarantee you
nothing bad will happen to her.

1233
01:36:05.600 --> 01:36:09.079
Besides. a night at the theatre...
Perhaps it'll be fun.

1234
01:36:14.080 --> 01:36:16.119
LAST PERFORMANCE

1235
01:37:17.760 --> 01:37:20.760
MUSIC BEGINS

1236
01:37:34.120 --> 01:37:37.639
I love to walk along via Toledo
and the seafront

1237
01:37:38.320 --> 01:37:41.799
All those handsome
young men in uniform

1238
01:37:42.320 --> 01:37:46.399
Who's that? Who is he?
What is he? Where is he?

1239
01:37:47.360 --> 01:37:49.319
Here's the handsome Fefe!

1240
01:37:50.680 --> 01:37:51.959
Fefe!

1241
01:37:53.160 --> 01:37:58.960
SHE SCREAMS

1242
01:38:04.680 --> 01:38:09.279
God is not a merchant
who pays on Saturday!

1243
01:38:09.720 --> 01:38:13.119
God is not a merchant
who pays on Saturday!

1244
01:38:13.240 --> 01:38:15.039
Who are you?
Where are you

1245
01:38:15.360 --> 01:38:17.119
Where are you?
What do you want from me?

1246
01:38:18.480 --> 01:38:19.559
Where are you?

1247
01:38:21.240 --> 01:38:22.719
What do you want from me?

1248
01:38:24.320 --> 01:38:25.919
- What do you want from me?
- Let me go!

1249
01:38:26.400 --> 01:38:28.439
Let me go! Let me go!

1250
01:38:40.960 --> 01:38:43.399
That old lady you found
was not my mother.

1251
01:38:46.320 --> 01:38:47.679
My mother is good.

1252
01:38:49.160 --> 01:38:50.719
She's always looked after me.

1253
01:38:51.800 --> 01:38:53.599
even when I was
in the institute.

1254
01:38:54.880 --> 01:38:56.319
She had to work.

1255
01:38:57.720 --> 01:39:00.599
She gives me everything.
She loves me.

1256
01:39:02.000 --> 01:39:03.959
And she always tells me
what to do.

1257
01:39:06.480 --> 01:39:08.759
She says not to tell anyone
I'm her son.

1258
01:39:09.720 --> 01:39:11.599
or people will think badly of me.

1259
01:39:14.600 --> 01:39:18.519
That's why I visit her at night. when
the caretaker turns out the light.

1260
01:39:20.440 --> 01:39:21.759
With Emma too.

1261
01:39:22.640 --> 01:39:24.039
She told me everything:

1262
01:39:25.000 --> 01:39:27.639
where to meet her.
what to tell her. everything.

1263
01:39:29.800 --> 01:39:31.359
She organised everything.

1264
01:39:33.280 --> 01:39:35.519
To steal money
and then to leave by car.

1265
01:39:37.040 --> 01:39:39.439
But then. one evening.

1266
01:39:41.360 --> 01:39:44.439
Emma suddenly said
we shouldn't see each other anymore.

1267
01:39:47.280 --> 01:39:48.959
I didn’t know what to say.

1268
01:39:51.400 --> 01:39:53.399
So that evening
I went to see my mother.

1269
01:39:54.400 --> 01:39:55.839
but I didn't find her.

1270
01:39:56.960 --> 01:40:00.919
I found an old witch who could
only talk about Emma's child.

1271
01:40:01.880 --> 01:40:04.679
Keep still a minute.
You're giving me a headache.

1272
01:40:05.360 --> 01:40:08.159
Walking bask and forth!
What do you want to tell me?

1273
01:40:08.560 --> 01:40:11.679
Nothing I do is any good.
What do you need? What do you want?

1274
01:40:11.800 --> 01:40:13.519
Mum. stop giving me orders.

1275
01:40:15.400 --> 01:40:17.759
- Did you tell Emma to stop seeing me?
- Yes. I did.

1276
01:40:18.720 --> 01:40:20.959
This child can grow up
in a rich family.

1277
01:40:21.080 --> 01:40:23.639
it can have a good life.
and we can't ruin that

1278
01:40:23.800 --> 01:40:26.519
Why. can't I become rich too?

1279
01:40:26.640 --> 01:40:30.079
It's not the same.
They've got an important surname.

1280
01:40:30.200 --> 01:40:33.239
And Emma's not just Emma anymore:
she's going to be a child's mother.

1281
01:40:33.400 --> 01:40:36.079
We can't touch them anymore.
Neither of them.

1282
01:40:36.360 --> 01:40:39.759
God is not a merchant
who pays on Saturday.

1283
01:40:41.920 --> 01:40:42.959
Come on!

1284
01:40:47.960 --> 01:40:50.039
You wretch!
Look what you've done!

1285
01:40:50.840 --> 01:40:52.519
What have you done?

1286
01:40:53.080 --> 01:40:56.959
Look what this wretch has done!
All my money on the ground!

1287
01:40:57.560 --> 01:40:59.119
Look what you've done

1288
01:41:01.100 --> 01:41:04.100
SCREAMING

1289
01:41:04.240 --> 01:41:05.240
That's enough!

1290
01:41:07.240 --> 01:41:09.879
And you come and tell me
that's my mother?

1291
01:41:11.360 --> 01:41:12.360
No.

1292
01:41:13.360 --> 01:41:14.799
That's the old witch.

1293
01:41:15.960 --> 01:41:19.839
So I drove her out of my mother.
I smashed open her head.

1294
01:41:24.560 --> 01:41:26.039
No. don't worry.

1295
01:41:26.560 --> 01:41:29.039
When my mother comes back.
everything will be fine.

1296
01:41:30.320 --> 01:41:32.079
She is blood of my blood!

1297
01:41:32.840 --> 01:41:35.640
HE SOBS

1298
01:41:35.880 --> 01:41:37.079
Come on!

1299
01:41:37.720 --> 01:41:38.879
Move.

1300
01:41:39.760 --> 01:41:41.319
Come on. you lowlife.

1301
01:41:58.880 --> 01:42:00.119
Inspector.

1302
01:42:05.120 --> 01:42:08.439
I have to thank you. because
you went all out to find the truth.

1303
01:42:08.560 --> 01:42:11.279
without letting anyone
influence you. not even me.

1304
01:42:12.400 --> 01:42:14.199
I staged
that whole ridiculous thing.

1305
01:42:15.160 --> 01:42:19.279
I went to Calise's house that evening.
planning to do who knows what.

1306
01:42:20.280 --> 01:42:23.879
But I found her there dead
and I got scared.

1307
01:42:26.160 --> 01:42:28.039
I'd made up my mind:

1308
01:42:28.920 --> 01:42:31.519
I'd take my life tonight
if Emma chose him.

1309
01:42:32.640 --> 01:42:34.319
But thanks to you.

1310
01:42:34.920 --> 01:42:39.279
Emma's realised she'd been blinded
by that madman and that fraudster.

1311
01:42:40.440 --> 01:42:42.999
And I've understood
that it's up to me

1312
01:42:43.480 --> 01:42:45.839
to get my life and
my marriage under control.

1313
01:42:47.600 --> 01:42:48.600
Thank you.

1314
01:42:53.480 --> 01:42:56.599
Sir! You see?
The pizza chef was innocent.

1315
01:42:56.760 --> 01:42:59.039
We have to thank
Mr Serra d'Arpaja and his wife.

1316
01:42:59.400 --> 01:43:03.319
who came to the theatre to help
pinpoint the guilty party.

1317
01:43:04.800 --> 01:43:07.359
No. I'm the one
who should thank you.

1318
01:43:07.520 --> 01:43:10.479
Congratulations. Deputy Garzo.
for your team's efficiency.

1319
01:43:10.600 --> 01:43:13.199
My duty. sir. my duty.

1320
01:43:13.680 --> 01:43:14.799
May I?

1321
01:43:15.200 --> 01:43:19.519
How come we never meet?
Don't you go to the club on Tuesdays?

1322
01:43:19.640 --> 01:43:21.879
Nice move.
Thank you. Maione.

1323
01:43:22.360 --> 01:43:23.759
It's nothing. Inspector.

1324
01:43:29.840 --> 01:43:32.559
I’m sorry to see you
like this recently. Inspector.

1325
01:43:33.960 --> 01:43:38.079
Not even solving a case and arresting
a crazy criminal can make you smile.

1326
01:43:42.840 --> 01:43:45.479
Can I ask you
a personal question?

1327
01:43:49.200 --> 01:43:50.839
Is it about the window?

1328
01:43:54.960 --> 01:43:57.679
Try to get some sleep.
we're both tired.

1329
01:43:58.240 --> 01:44:00.919
- Hope I can sleep too.
- Keep it open.

1330
01:44:05.080 --> 01:44:07.039
The window. I mean.

1331
01:44:09.560 --> 01:44:11.439
Spring is here. Inspector.

1332
01:44:13.680 --> 01:44:15.159
You never know.

1333
01:44:18.000 --> 01:44:19.199
Good night.

1334
01:44:29.560 --> 01:44:31.559
No. I can't waste any more time.

1335
01:44:32.240 --> 01:44:34.439
In fact. I've decided
to take your advice.

1336
01:44:36.080 --> 01:44:38.319
I'm going
to a resort this summer.

1337
01:44:40.040 --> 01:44:41.839
No. it's already organised.

1338
01:44:43.800 --> 01:44:47.599
If things go the way as planned.
it might be a long stay at the resort.

1339
01:44:51.640 --> 01:44:53.239
My sensitive man?

1340
01:44:54.800 --> 01:44:56.599
He's the one I'm going to.

1341
01:44:59.240 --> 01:45:00.919
Even if he doesn't know it yet.

1342
01:45:08.160 --> 01:45:10.160
TALKING ON RADIO

1343
01:45:10.200 --> 01:45:11.200
DOOR CLOSES

1344
01:49:14.160 --> 01:49:17.160
Subtitles for the deaf
and hard of hearing by Red Bee Media
